{"type":"text","timestamp":1778610735008,"sessionID":"ses_1e28cc825ffen1kBKXgZgaDxSY","part":{"id":"prt_e1d760521001qM2sK6OvEENwy5","messageID":"msg_e1d73f931001VDGi7uFca8BDdR","sessionID":"ses_1e28cc825ffen1kBKXgZgaDxSY","type":"text","text":"I’m going to write a single micro-opt hypothesis around removing unnecessary reset mux/fanout from datapath pipeline and M-unit flops while keeping all side-effecting control/valid bits reset-safe.","time":{"start":1778610734369,"end":1778610735007},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0fa6092e65397f83016a03722e3da08195a1a198e40771c158","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778610756966,"sessionID":"ses_1e28cc825ffen1kBKXgZgaDxSY","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_NdknNR5APWatd07MqfMjMUbh","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r10s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r10s0\n+title: \"Control-only datapath resets\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  Recent bench wins have come from small Fmax-oriented cleanups that avoid new\n+  prediction, bypass, or frontend machinery. The current RTL still resets large\n+  datapath payloads in ID/EX, EX/MEM, MEM/WB, and the RV32M side units even\n+  though only valid/control bits are required to suppress retirement, writes,\n+  redirects, and memory side effects after reset or flush.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Convert pipeline and M-unit reset handling to reset only valid, state, and\n+  side-effecting control fields while leaving operand/result/PC/data payload\n+  flops unreset when their associated valid/control bits are clear. Flushes and\n+  reset bubbles must still clear ctrl.mem_read, ctrl.mem_write, ctrl.reg_write,\n+  ctrl.is_branch, ctrl.is_jump, and valid so invalid instructions cannot retire,\n+  redirect, or touch memory. This should reduce synchronous-reset muxing and\n+  global reset fanout across hundreds of FPGA flops without changing pipeline\n+  depth, CoreMark cycle count, RVFI order, or trap behavior.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Change ID/EX reset and flush bubbles to clear valid and control fields only, leaving data payload flops unreset when invalid.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Change EX/MEM reset bubbles and slow-M emitted bubbles to clear valid/control side-effect fields only while keeping operand/result payload flops off the reset network.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Change MEM/WB reset bubbles to clear valid/control writeback fields only, preserving hold_wb semantics and preventing invalid retirements or writes.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mul_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Remove reset from the registered MUL result payload while still resetting result_valid so stale products are never consumed.\"\n+  - file: rtl/m_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Remove reset from slow RV32M datapath payload registers while keeping state, counters, busy/result_valid, and control reset-safe for formal liveness.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r10s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r10s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r10s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r10s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,32 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r10s0\n+title: \"Control-only datapath resets\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  Recent bench wins have come from small Fmax-oriented cleanups that avoid new\n+  prediction, bypass, or frontend machinery. The current RTL still resets large\n+  datapath payloads in ID/EX, EX/MEM, MEM/WB, and the RV32M side units even\n+  though only valid/control bits are required to suppress retirement, writes,\n+  redirects, and memory side effects after reset or flush.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Convert pipeline and M-unit reset handling to reset only valid, state, and\n+  side-effecting control fields while leaving operand/result/PC/data payload\n+  flops unreset when their associated valid/control bits are clear. Flushes and\n+  reset bubbles must still clear ctrl.mem_read, ctrl.mem_write, ctrl.reg_write,\n+  ctrl.is_branch, ctrl.is_jump, and valid so invalid instructions cannot retire,\n+  redirect, or touch memory. This should reduce synchronous-reset muxing and\n+  global reset fanout across hundreds of FPGA flops without changing pipeline\n+  depth, CoreMark cycle count, RVFI order, or trap behavior.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Change ID/EX reset and flush bubbles to clear valid and control fields only, leaving data payload flops unreset when invalid.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Change EX/MEM reset bubbles and slow-M emitted bubbles to clear valid/control side-effect fields only while keeping operand/result payload flops off the reset network.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Change MEM/WB reset bubbles to clear valid/control writeback fields only, preserving hold_wb semantics and preventing invalid retirements or writes.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mul_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Remove reset from the registered MUL result payload while still resetting result_valid so stale products are never consumed.\"\n+  - file: rtl/m_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Remove reset from slow RV32M datapath payload registers while keeping state, counters, busy/result_valid, and control reset-safe for formal liveness.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r10s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r10s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r10s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r10s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r10s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,32 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r10s0\n+title: \"Control-only datapath resets\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  Recent bench wins have come from small Fmax-oriented cleanups that avoid new\n+  prediction, bypass, or frontend machinery. The current RTL still resets large\n+  datapath payloads in ID/EX, EX/MEM, MEM/WB, and the RV32M side units even\n+  though only valid/control bits are required to suppress retirement, writes,\n+  redirects, and memory side effects after reset or flush.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Convert pipeline and M-unit reset handling to reset only valid, state, and\n+  side-effecting control fields while leaving operand/result/PC/data payload\n+  flops unreset when their associated valid/control bits are clear. Flushes and\n+  reset bubbles must still clear ctrl.mem_read, ctrl.mem_write, ctrl.reg_write,\n+  ctrl.is_branch, ctrl.is_jump, and valid so invalid instructions cannot retire,\n+  redirect, or touch memory. This should reduce synchronous-reset muxing and\n+  global reset fanout across hundreds of FPGA flops without changing pipeline\n+  depth, CoreMark cycle count, RVFI order, or trap behavior.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Change ID/EX reset and flush bubbles to clear valid and control fields only, leaving data payload flops unreset when invalid.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Change EX/MEM reset bubbles and slow-M emitted bubbles to clear valid/control side-effect fields only while keeping operand/result payload flops off the reset network.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Change MEM/WB reset bubbles to clear valid/control writeback fields only, preserving hold_wb semantics and preventing invalid retirements or writes.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mul_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Remove reset from the registered MUL result payload while still resetting result_valid so stale products are never consumed.\"\n+  - file: rtl/m_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Remove reset from slow RV32M datapath payload registers while keeping state, counters, busy/result_valid, and control reset-safe for formal liveness.\"\n","additions":32,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r10s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778610756962,"end":1778610756965}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0fa6092e65397f83016a03722eed488195a809c119ad2dc072"}},"id":"prt_e1d7607a00013tIg4SoLndROYj","sessionID":"ses_1e28cc825ffen1kBKXgZgaDxSY","messageID":"msg_e1d73f931001VDGi7uFca8BDdR"}}
