{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778610764777,"sessionID":"ses_1e28cc825ffen1kBKXgZgaDxSY","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_JodFMeXlSWSBYq8941rGYC8t","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r10s0.yaml","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r10s0.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: hyp-20260512-001-r10s0\n2: title: \"Control-only datapath resets\"\n3: category: micro_opt\n4: motivation: |\n5:   Recent bench wins have come from small Fmax-oriented cleanups that avoid new\n6:   prediction, bypass, or frontend machinery. The current RTL still resets large\n7:   datapath payloads in ID/EX, EX/MEM, MEM/WB, and the RV32M side units even\n8:   though only valid/control bits are required to suppress retirement, writes,\n9:   redirects, and memory side effects after reset or flush.\n10: hypothesis: |\n11:   Convert pipeline and M-unit reset handling to reset only valid, state, and\n12:   side-effecting control fields while leaving operand/result/PC/data payload\n13:   flops unreset when their associated valid/control bits are clear. Flushes and\n14:   reset bubbles must still clear ctrl.mem_read, ctrl.mem_write, ctrl.reg_write,\n15:   ctrl.is_branch, ctrl.is_jump, and valid so invalid instructions cannot retire,\n16:   redirect, or touch memory. This should reduce synchronous-reset muxing and\n17:   global reset fanout across hundreds of FPGA flops without changing pipeline\n18:   depth, CoreMark cycle count, RVFI order, or trap behavior.\n19: expected_impact:\n20:   fitness_delta_pct: 2\n21:   confidence: medium\n22: changes:\n23:   - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n24:     description: \"Change ID/EX reset and flush bubbles to clear valid and control fields only, leaving data payload flops unreset when invalid.\"\n25:   - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n26:     description: \"Change EX/MEM reset bubbles and slow-M emitted bubbles to clear valid/control side-effect fields only while keeping operand/result payload flops off the reset network.\"\n27:   - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n28:     description: \"Change MEM/WB reset bubbles to clear valid/control writeback fields only, preserving hold_wb semantics and preventing invalid retirements or writes.\"\n29:   - file: rtl/mul_unit.sv\n30:     description: \"Remove reset from the registered MUL result payload while still resetting result_valid so stale products are never consumed.\"\n31:   - file: rtl/m_unit.sv\n32:     description: \"Remove reset from slow RV32M datapath payload registers while keeping state, counters, busy/result_valid, and control reset-safe for formal liveness.\"\n\n(End of file - total 32 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260512-001-r10s0\ntitle: \"Control-only datapath resets\"\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  Recent bench wins have come from small Fmax-oriented cleanups that avoid new\n  prediction, bypass, or frontend machinery. The current RTL still resets large\n  datapath payloads in ID/EX, EX/MEM, MEM/WB, and the RV32M side units even\n  though only valid/control bits are required to suppress retirement, writes,\n  redirects, and memory side effects after reset or flush.\nhypothesis: |\n  Convert pipeline and M-unit reset handling to reset only valid, state, and\n  side-effecting control fields while leaving operand/result/PC/data payload\n  flops unreset when their associated valid/control bits are clear. Flushes and\n  reset bubbles must still clear ctrl.mem_read, ctrl.mem_write, ctrl.reg_write,\n  ctrl.is_branch, ctrl.is_jump, and valid so invalid instructions cannot retire,\n  redirect, or touch memory. This should reduce synchronous-reset muxing and\n  global reset fanout across hundreds of FPGA flops without changing pipeline\n  depth, CoreMark cycle count, RVFI order, or trap behavior.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 2","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r10s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778610764768,"end":1778610764776}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0481ca9da2f0291b016a03724af030819497df4caafb8edb10"}},"id":"prt_e1d767517001nEb9jTs4eOaJWv","sessionID":"ses_1e28cc825ffen1kBKXgZgaDxSY","messageID":"msg_e1d765df5001DibHt7Trowvu1i"}}
