{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1778612540142,"sessionID":"ses_1e26ef11fffer8rvtp4nIilBKZ","part":{"id":"prt_e1d9192ec001NoBQT6TjVgAytF","messageID":"msg_e1d91848b001JB8WWtdJJpNJ0I","sessionID":"ses_1e26ef11fffer8rvtp4nIilBKZ","snapshot":"213eb72c2f32b9221edafd5accb912070e059c58","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1778612687121,"sessionID":"ses_1e26ef11fffer8rvtp4nIilBKZ","part":{"id":"prt_e1d93c7ca001U7ZjX18EW5vrKh","messageID":"msg_e1d91848b001JB8WWtdJJpNJ0I","sessionID":"ses_1e26ef11fffer8rvtp4nIilBKZ","type":"text","text":"The useful prior micro-opt pattern is still Fmax-only cleanup without new state: forwarding-select retiming and registered MUL helped, while predictors, bypasses, reset reshaping, and result-predictor exceptions regressed. I’m going to write a narrow EX-stage hypothesis that shares existing PC adders and moves the rare AUIPC selection off the ALU input path without changing pipeline depth or adding sideband state.","time":{"start":1778612684746,"end":1778612687119},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0246858c107124ea016a0379cc992c8193833bffaa87239d77","phase":"commentary"}}}}
