{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778612716000,"sessionID":"ses_1e26ef11fffer8rvtp4nIilBKZ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_VTr14BbhtHjxlD8SSwsrNSbX","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r11s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r11s0\n+title: \"Share EX PC adders\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The best bench-core results have come from small Fmax-oriented changes that\n+  keep the pipeline shape unchanged and avoid new prediction, bypass, or\n+  exception fast paths. The current EX stage still recomputes pc+imm for both\n+  branch/JAL target handling and AUIPC, recomputes pc+4 for link and fall-through\n+  paths, and places a rare AUIPC-controlled 32-bit mux in front of the fast ALU\n+  operand path used by ordinary ADD, load/store address generation, and branch\n+  work. The prior PC-precompute attempt regressed because it added ID-side\n+  adders and wider ID/EX state; this narrower cleanup keeps the adders local to\n+  EX and only removes duplicated source expressions and a hot input mux.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  In rtl/ex_stage.sv, create local shared pc_plus4 and pc_imm_sum wires and use\n+  them for branch targets, JAL targets, AUIPC rd_wdata, JAL/JALR link data, and\n+  pc_next fall-through. At the same time, remove the is_auipc selection from the\n+  ALU input mux so normal ALU and load/store address operations feed rs1 directly\n+  into the ALU; AUIPC should select the shared pc_imm_sum only at the EX/MEM\n+  result boundary. This should shorten the common EX operand-to-ALU cone without\n+  adding pipeline registers, changing CoreMark cycle count, changing slow-M/MUL\n+  handshakes, or affecting the nret=1 RVFI retirement contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Share pc+4 and pc+imm calculations locally in EX, use the shared pc+imm result for AUIPC/JAL/branch paths, and move AUIPC selection from the ALU input mux to the EX/MEM result mux.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r11s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r11s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r11s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r11s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,28 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r11s0\n+title: \"Share EX PC adders\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The best bench-core results have come from small Fmax-oriented changes that\n+  keep the pipeline shape unchanged and avoid new prediction, bypass, or\n+  exception fast paths. The current EX stage still recomputes pc+imm for both\n+  branch/JAL target handling and AUIPC, recomputes pc+4 for link and fall-through\n+  paths, and places a rare AUIPC-controlled 32-bit mux in front of the fast ALU\n+  operand path used by ordinary ADD, load/store address generation, and branch\n+  work. The prior PC-precompute attempt regressed because it added ID-side\n+  adders and wider ID/EX state; this narrower cleanup keeps the adders local to\n+  EX and only removes duplicated source expressions and a hot input mux.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  In rtl/ex_stage.sv, create local shared pc_plus4 and pc_imm_sum wires and use\n+  them for branch targets, JAL targets, AUIPC rd_wdata, JAL/JALR link data, and\n+  pc_next fall-through. At the same time, remove the is_auipc selection from the\n+  ALU input mux so normal ALU and load/store address operations feed rs1 directly\n+  into the ALU; AUIPC should select the shared pc_imm_sum only at the EX/MEM\n+  result boundary. This should shorten the common EX operand-to-ALU cone without\n+  adding pipeline registers, changing CoreMark cycle count, changing slow-M/MUL\n+  handshakes, or affecting the nret=1 RVFI retirement contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Share pc+4 and pc+imm calculations locally in EX, use the shared pc+imm result for AUIPC/JAL/branch paths, and move AUIPC selection from the ALU input mux to the EX/MEM result mux.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r11s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r11s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r11s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r11s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r11s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,28 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r11s0\n+title: \"Share EX PC adders\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The best bench-core results have come from small Fmax-oriented changes that\n+  keep the pipeline shape unchanged and avoid new prediction, bypass, or\n+  exception fast paths. The current EX stage still recomputes pc+imm for both\n+  branch/JAL target handling and AUIPC, recomputes pc+4 for link and fall-through\n+  paths, and places a rare AUIPC-controlled 32-bit mux in front of the fast ALU\n+  operand path used by ordinary ADD, load/store address generation, and branch\n+  work. The prior PC-precompute attempt regressed because it added ID-side\n+  adders and wider ID/EX state; this narrower cleanup keeps the adders local to\n+  EX and only removes duplicated source expressions and a hot input mux.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  In rtl/ex_stage.sv, create local shared pc_plus4 and pc_imm_sum wires and use\n+  them for branch targets, JAL targets, AUIPC rd_wdata, JAL/JALR link data, and\n+  pc_next fall-through. At the same time, remove the is_auipc selection from the\n+  ALU input mux so normal ALU and load/store address operations feed rs1 directly\n+  into the ALU; AUIPC should select the shared pc_imm_sum only at the EX/MEM\n+  result boundary. This should shorten the common EX operand-to-ALU cone without\n+  adding pipeline registers, changing CoreMark cycle count, changing slow-M/MUL\n+  handshakes, or affecting the nret=1 RVFI retirement contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Share pc+4 and pc+imm calculations locally in EX, use the shared pc+imm result for AUIPC/JAL/branch paths, and move AUIPC selection from the ALU input mux to the EX/MEM result mux.\"\n","additions":28,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r11s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778612715994,"end":1778612715999}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_02b0e8bf802615f7016a0379d92aa48195b42491695cf7f3ea"}},"id":"prt_e1d93f8a4001n5akYEc8oBf9ft","sessionID":"ses_1e26ef11fffer8rvtp4nIilBKZ","messageID":"msg_e1d93da4c001rwda0yLea0wUsS"}}
