voiding live predictor lookup,\\nimmediate decode, and target addition on ordinary fall-through fetch cycles.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitne... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260512-001-r10s0\", \"title\": \"Control-only datapath resets\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"motivation\": \"Recent bench wins have come from small Fmax-oriented cleanups that avoid new\\nprediction, bypass, or frontend machinery. The current RTL still resets large\\ndatapath payloads in ID/EX, EX/MEM, MEM/WB, and the RV32M side units even\\nthough only valid/control bits are required to suppress retirement, writes,\\nredirects, and memory side effects after reset or flush.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"Recent bench wins have come from small Fmax-oriented cleanups that avoid new\\nprediction, bypass, or frontend machinery. The current RTL still resets large\\ndatapath payloads in ID/EX, EX/MEM, MEM/WB, and the RV32M side units even\\nthough only valid/control bits are required to suppress retirement, writes,\\nredirects, and memory side effects after reset or flush.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Convert pipeline and M-unit reset handling to reset only valid, state, and\\nside-effecting control fields while leaving operand/result/PC/data payload\\nflops unreset when their associated valid/control bits are clear. Flushes and\\nreset bubbles must still clear ctrl.mem_read, ctrl.mem_write, ctrl.reg_write,\\nctrl.is_branch, ctrl.is_jump, and valid so invalid instructions cannot retire,\\nredirect, or touch memory. This should reduce synchronous-reset muxing and\\nglobal reset fanout across hundreds of FPGA flops without changing pipeline\\ndepth, CoreMark cycle count, RVFI order, or trap behavior.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 2, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Change ID/EX reset and flush bubbles to clear valid and control fields only, leaving data payload flops unreset when invalid.\"}