{"type":"text","timestamp":1778616498103,"sessionID":"ses_1e2326609ffe1ZrUhwfxdr3VMl","part":{"id":"prt_e1dcde74b001ZKQwZ27bXwNJ1m","messageID":"msg_e1dcdd3240017SfZXDejrrvyJ7","sessionID":"ses_1e2326609ffe1ZrUhwfxdr3VMl","type":"text","text":"The history points away from predictors, memory bypasses, partial-product MULs, PC-precompute, and extra forwarding state. The remaining promising `micro_opt` angle is a localized timing cleanup that reduces EX-stage immediate/decoder fanout without changing IPC: specialize the ALU input/result handling for LUI so the generic ALU adder/logic cone no longer carries the U-immediate path.","time":{"start":1778616493899,"end":1778616498100},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0a093447d3bce74d016a0388adc6f4819b8989df6f801de269","phase":"commentary"}}}}
