{"type":"text","timestamp":1778616624699,"sessionID":"ses_1e2326609ffe1ZrUhwfxdr3VMl","part":{"id":"prt_e1dcfe6340016T9ptSj8c7lbY9","messageID":"msg_e1dcdf84d001BU0Zxm9d2HS6k4","sessionID":"ses_1e2326609ffe1ZrUhwfxdr3VMl","type":"text","text":"I’m writing the hypothesis as a focused `mul_unit.sv` retiming proposal: keep the successful isolated low-half MUL side path, but add an input-register stage instead of partial-product decomposition or sharing with the slow M unit.","time":{"start":1778616624692,"end":1778616624696},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_05e7a7b84ea89c52016a038930682c819994168a912f27f35a","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778616629905,"sessionID":"ses_1e2326609ffe1ZrUhwfxdr3VMl","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_CwgiyJIXDz4227R1ncLZY2R2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r13s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r13s0\n+title: Input-registered low MUL\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The best current bench result came from isolating low-half MUL from the\n+  common EX ALU cone, while later attempts showed that partial-product MUL,\n+  shared M-unit dispatch, and trivial operand bypasses add too much control or\n+  arithmetic structure. The remaining MUL-specific timing risk is the direct\n+  forwarded-operand-to-32x32-product path inside the standalone mul_unit.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Retiming only the real low-half MUL path with an operand capture stage should\n+  preserve the successful single inferred 32x32 product while shortening its\n+  input cone. On start, mul_unit would latch operands and mark itself busy;\n+  the following cycle computes and registers the product from those stable\n+  operands, then presents the existing result_valid/result_ready handshake to\n+  EX. This adds one extra cycle only to sparse CoreMark MUL instructions, avoids\n+  reintroducing multiplier logic into the fast ALU path, and avoids the failed\n+  16x16 partial-product decomposition.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/mul_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add a real-hardware operand register/busy phase before the inferred 32x32 low-half product, preserving the existing handshake and ALTOPS behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Adjust or verify low-half MUL start/busy/result_ready sequencing still holds ID/EX exactly until the retimed mul_unit result is valid.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r13s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r13s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r13s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r13s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,26 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r13s0\n+title: Input-registered low MUL\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The best current bench result came from isolating low-half MUL from the\n+  common EX ALU cone, while later attempts showed that partial-product MUL,\n+  shared M-unit dispatch, and trivial operand bypasses add too much control or\n+  arithmetic structure. The remaining MUL-specific timing risk is the direct\n+  forwarded-operand-to-32x32-product path inside the standalone mul_unit.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Retiming only the real low-half MUL path with an operand capture stage should\n+  preserve the successful single inferred 32x32 product while shortening its\n+  input cone. On start, mul_unit would latch operands and mark itself busy;\n+  the following cycle computes and registers the product from those stable\n+  operands, then presents the existing result_valid/result_ready handshake to\n+  EX. This adds one extra cycle only to sparse CoreMark MUL instructions, avoids\n+  reintroducing multiplier logic into the fast ALU path, and avoids the failed\n+  16x16 partial-product decomposition.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/mul_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add a real-hardware operand register/busy phase before the inferred 32x32 low-half product, preserving the existing handshake and ALTOPS behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    d