{"type":"text","timestamp":1778617782575,"sessionID":"ses_1e21fe846ffeE0r2BE0eeYZ1Ek","part":{"id":"prt_e1de190e0001HheweS0KBSMODj","messageID":"msg_e1de13b5d0013Z3js0TsujTcOe","sessionID":"ses_1e21fe846ffeE0r2BE0eeYZ1Ek","type":"text","text":"I’m writing the hypothesis as a narrow regfile reset optimization, explicitly avoiding the earlier duplicated-LUTRAM rewrite that regressed.","time":{"start":1778617782496,"end":1778617782574},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_048f91722ad8fd83016a038db6671481978352b137a5bf74fc","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778617788775,"sessionID":"ses_1e21fe846ffeE0r2BE0eeYZ1Ek","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_qEJFsM7qkrspe8x3KvrlobDm","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r14s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r14s0\n+title: \"Drop regfile reset fanout\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  Recent micro_opt attempts show that added forwarding, predictor, and result\n+  mux control usually costs more Fmax than it saves in CoreMark cycles. The\n+  register file still has a large synchronous reset loop over all 32 x 32 bits,\n+  even though RV32IM only architecturally requires x0 to read as zero and the\n+  benchmark startup code initializes the live registers it uses.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Remove the reset clearing loop from rtl/reg_file.sv while preserving the\n+  existing single-array storage shape, x0 hardwire behavior, and same-cycle\n+  write-first bypass. This is narrower than the failed duplicated LUTRAM\n+  regfile rewrite: it does not add read-bank replication, write fanout, or new\n+  decode muxing. Dropping the non-architectural GPR reset should remove roughly\n+  one thousand reset mux/load points and may let synthesis pack or route the\n+  regfile more efficiently, improving Fmax without changing IPC, RVFI order,\n+  memory behavior, or the nret=1 top-level contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/reg_file.sv\n+    description: \"Remove synchronous clearing of writable GPRs on reset while retaining the x0 hardwire and write-first bypass; keep the storage topology otherwise unchanged to avoid the failed duplicated-LUTRAM rewrite.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r14s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhi