{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1778618556658,"sessionID":"ses_1e212da49ffej86GRvXv1270PJ","part":{"id":"prt_e1ded60f1001Eur5D0fZry1rQr","messageID":"msg_e1ded5b7500175GxvYw2VUJI3g","sessionID":"ses_1e212da49ffej86GRvXv1270PJ","snapshot":"feebd66371e5f8944ad3a795fec540653e32c701","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1778618617538,"sessionID":"ses_1e212da49ffej86GRvXv1270PJ","part":{"id":"prt_e1dee4d4c0015AR8EPTAzzRY8d","messageID":"msg_e1ded5b7500175GxvYw2VUJI3g","sessionID":"ses_1e212da49ffej86GRvXv1270PJ","type":"text","text":"The prior micro-opt wins were Fmax-driven and localized (`m_unit` finalization, isolated registered MUL). Recent failures show that broader control, RVFI, regfile, predictor, and forwarding changes usually lose QoR, so I’m choosing a narrow slow-divider retiming target that does not touch the hot fetch/forwarding paths.","time":{"start":1778618617164,"end":1778618617537},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0e238013a6e5748f016a0390f90468819abc7081f68f14ebe3","phase":"commentary"}}}}
