{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778594958949,"sessionID":"ses_1e37ea091ffeyMqgpxioIN6QjM","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_IPQMLADl8qyBCcRvgQLtmkGv","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r1s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r1s0\n+title: \"Share RV32M ALU datapaths\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The bench core's EX ALU currently computes three 64-bit products plus\n+  independent signed/unsigned divide and remainder expressions before selecting\n+  one result. Even when CoreMark mostly exercises simple ALU and MUL paths,\n+  those wide arithmetic blocks remain in the EX output cone and add LUT and\n+  routing pressure on the Tang Nano 20K. Reducing redundant arithmetic should\n+  improve median Fmax without adding cycles to the common MUL path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Rewrite the real RV32M branch of rtl/alu.sv so all multiply variants use one\n+  sign-configurable 33x33 product, and all DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU variants share\n+  normalized unsigned quotient/remainder logic with the existing RISC-V\n+  divide-by-zero and overflow fixups. Keep the RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS substitutions\n+  equivalent and preserve single-cycle ALU latency, so CoreMark IPC should not\n+  regress while the FPGA critical path and LUT/routing pressure improve.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Replace parallel RV32M multiply/divide expressions with shared sign-normalized combinational datapaths while preserving ALTOPS and RV32M corner-case semantics.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Add or retain focused RV32M corner vectors for MULH/MULHSU/MULHU and DIV/REM divide-by-zero/overflow cases to guard the shared datapath rewrite.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r1s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r1s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r1s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r1s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,25 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r1s0\n+title: \"Share RV32M ALU datapaths\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The bench core's EX ALU currently computes three 64-bit products plus\n+  independent signed/unsigned divide and remainder expressions before selecting\n+  one result. Even when CoreMark mostly exercises simple ALU and MUL paths,\n+  those wide arithmetic blocks remain in the EX output cone and add LUT and\n+  routing pressure on the Tang Nano 20K. Reducing redundant arithmetic should\n+  improve median Fmax without adding cycles to the common MUL path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Rewrite the real RV32M branch of rtl/alu.sv so all multiply variants use one\n+  sign-configurable 33x33 product, and all DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU variants share\n+  normalized unsigned quotient/remainder logic with the existing RISC-V\n+  divide-by-zero and overflow fixups. Keep the RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS substitutions\n+  equivalent and preserve single-cycle ALU latency, so CoreMark IPC should not\n+  regress while the FPGA critical path and LUT/routing pressure improve.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Replace parallel RV32M multiply/divide expressions with shared sign-normalized combinational datapaths while preserving ALTOPS and RV32M corner-case semantics.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Add or retain focused RV32M corner vectors for MULH/MULHSU/MULHU and 