{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778596743622,"sessionID":"ses_1e362936fffedm6C3qmHOFrY5W","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_5hZVULseRE1bGyCYEb8XFfDe","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r2s0.yaml","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r2s0.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: hyp-20260512-001-r2s0\n2: title: \"Trim low-half MUL partial products\"\n3: category: micro_opt\n4: motivation: |\n5:   The current best design already removed rare high-half multiply and divide\n6:   operations from the common EX result cone, but RV32M low-half MUL remains a\n7:   single-cycle 32x32 multiply in the fast ALU. CoreMark benefits from keeping\n8:   MUL single-cycle, yet RV32 MUL only needs product bits [31:0], so the high x\n9:   high partial product and some upper carry logic are unnecessary FPGA work.\n10: hypothesis: |\n11:   Replace the generic low-half `a * b` implementation in rtl/alu.sv with an\n12:   explicit low-32 partial-product decomposition using 16-bit limbs: low x low\n13:   plus the lower half of the two cross products shifted by 16. This should let\n14:   synthesis drop the unused high x high multiplier work and map the remaining\n15:   pieces more cleanly to Tang Nano DSP/LUT resources while preserving the\n16:   one-cycle ALU_MUL latency that CoreMark needs. Keep the RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS\n17:   substitute unchanged and add focused MUL low-half carry vectors so RV32M\n18:   bit-exactness remains covered.\n19: expected_impact:\n20:   fitness_delta_pct: 4\n21:   confidence: medium\n22: changes:\n23:   - file: rtl/alu.sv\n24:     description: \"Compute ALU_MUL's low 32 bits from 16-bit partial products instead of a full generic 32x32 product, leaving ALTOPS behavior unchanged.\"\n25:   - file: test/test_alu.py\n26:     description: \"Add MUL low-half edge vectors that exercise cross-product carries and discarded high-half bits.\"\n\n(End of file - total 26 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260512-001-r2s0\ntitle: \"Trim low-half MUL partial products\"\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  The current best design already removed rare high-half multiply and divide\n  operations from the common EX result cone, but RV32M low-half MUL remains a\n  single-cycle 32x32 multiply in the fast ALU. CoreMark benefits from keeping\n  MUL single-cycle, yet RV32 MUL only needs product bits [31:0], so the high x\n  high partial product and some upper carry logic are unnecessary FPGA work.\nhypothesis: |\n  Replace the generic low-half `a * b` implementation in rtl/alu.sv with an\n  explicit low-32 partial-product decomposition using 16-bit limbs: low x low\n  plus the lower half of the two cross products shifted by 16. This should let\n  synthesis drop the unused high x high multiplier work and map the remaining\n  pieces more cleanly to Tang Nano DSP/LUT resources while preserving the\n  one-cycle ALU_MUL latency that CoreMark needs. Keep the RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS\n  substitute unchanged and add focused MUL low-half carry vectors so RV32M\n  bit-exactness remains covered.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 4","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r2s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778596743616,"end":1778596743621}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0043a57b1cec104c016a033b8728e08197a7a0ab34cc969c42"}},"id":"prt_e1ca08860001wqZuM6vx52w8P1","sessionID":"ses_1e362936fffedm6C3qmHOFrY5W","messageID":"msg_e1ca02992001IwzbjtiYwLeKBl"}}
