{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778598816763,"sessionID":"ses_1e3435330ffeZ7xtz7orT3oGDf","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_EDfqUSRETGBbkdhSPHRFpTA4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r3s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r3s0\n+title: \"Retiming slow M finalization\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best design already moved high-half multiply and divide/remainder\n+  out of the common EX ALU path, but the multi-cycle m_unit still participates\n+  in FPGA timing. Its final MULH and DIV/REM cycles combine iterative\n+  add/subtract work with sign correction and result selection, creating long\n+  carry/mux cones for operations that CoreMark rarely executes.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add one explicit finish state to the slow RV32M unit so the last iterative\n+  step captures an unsigned product, quotient, or remainder, and a following\n+  cycle performs any two's-complement sign correction and result muxing. This\n+  increases latency only for rare slow M operations while shortening the\n+  m_unit register-to-register critical paths, preserving the one-cycle\n+  low-half MUL fast path and the CoreMark IPC profile.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/m_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Split final sign correction/result selection for MULH and DIV/REM into a separate registered finish cycle, leaving ALTOPS and low-half MUL behavior unchanged.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Retain or add RV32M corner vectors for signed high-half multiply and signed DIV/REM overflow/negative cases to verify the retimed finish state.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r3s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/