{"type":"text","timestamp":1778601678578,"sessionID":"ses_1e31752b1ffeBJruno34LH2hjx","part":{"id":"prt_e1cebd570001u9uvdyXtI65dzo","messageID":"msg_e1ce92516001Xdw26EFxJD7nN5","sessionID":"ses_1e31752b1ffeBJruno34LH2hjx","type":"text","text":"Prior micro-opt attempts mainly targeted RV32M datapath retiming and MEM byte-lane logic. The least-overlapping opportunity is source-aware load-use qualification: remove false bubbles when raw `rs1/rs2` bitfields match a preceding load but the decoded instruction does not architecturally read that operand.","time":{"start":1778601678192,"end":1778601678577},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0e1b49e5d24653c8016a034ece0d4c8197afd59c6ecf7a0b59","phase":"commentary"}}}}
