{"type":"text","timestamp":1778603332940,"sessionID":"ses_1e2fed72dffedwCt0MPGHEd9FM","part":{"id":"prt_e1d050ff40023Uy0yDI1f6Q8FX","messageID":"msg_e1d04bf0e001iiJgS5bE9nFHig","sessionID":"ses_1e2fed72dffedwCt0MPGHEd9FM","type":"text","text":"Writing a single micro-opt hypothesis that retimes deterministic PC-relative adds into the ID/EX boundary, avoiding the failed predictor-style IF feedback path while shortening EX datapaths.","time":{"start":1778603331572,"end":1778603332939},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0610447861de266b016a0355437de08196bb012708a4e9efc0","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778603352415,"sessionID":"ses_1e2fed72dffedwCt0MPGHEd9FM","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_JnKdPZ5j5vmfpC81P19HxPdU","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r6s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r6s0\n+title: \"Precompute PC-relative EX values\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best results indicate that fitness gains are coming from Fmax,\n+  not from added prediction or bypass IPC. The EX stage still recomputes\n+  pc+4 and pc+imm for branch, JAL, JALR link, and AUIPC handling, and it keeps\n+  an is_auipc mux in front of the fast ALU operand path. Those deterministic\n+  PC-relative values can be registered before EX instead of sitting in the\n+  ALU/MUL and redirect timing cones.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add registered pc_plus4 and pc_imm fields to the ID/EX payload, computed in\n+  id_stage from the existing immediate generator output. Use those registered\n+  values in ex_stage for direct branch and JAL targets, AUIPC rd_wdata,\n+  JAL/JALR link writeback, and fall-through pc_next. JALR target calculation\n+  remains in EX because it depends on the forwarded rs1 operand. This should\n+  remove PC adders and the AUIPC operand mux from hot EX paths without changing\n+  pipeline depth, stall policy, RVFI ordering, or CoreMark cycle count.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add registered pc_plus4 and pc_imm fields to id_ex_t so PC-relative values are available in EX without recomputation.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute pc_plus4 and pc_imm while latching ID/EX, using the existing immediate generator output and preserving flush/stall behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Use the registered PC-relative fields for branch/JAL targets, AUIPC results, link writeback, and pc_next while keeping JALR target calculation in EX.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r6s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r6s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r6s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r6s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,28 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r6s0\n+title: \"Precompute PC-relative EX values\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best results indicate that fitness gains are coming from Fmax,\n+  not from added prediction or bypass IPC. The EX stage still recomputes\n+  pc+4 and pc+imm for branch, JAL, JALR link, and AUIPC handling, and it keeps\n+  an is_auipc mux in front of the fast ALU operand path. Those deterministic\n+  PC-relative values can be registered before EX instead of sitting in the\n+  ALU/MUL and redirect timing cones.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add registered pc_plus4 and pc_imm fields to the ID/EX payload, computed in\n+  id_stage from the existing immediate generator output. Use those registered\n+  values in ex_stage for direct branch and JAL targets, AUIPC rd_wdata,\n+  JAL/JALR link writeback, and fall-through pc_next. JALR target calculation\n+  remains in EX because it depends on the forwarded rs1 operand. This should\n+  remove PC adders and the AUIPC operand mux from hot EX paths without changing\n+  pipeline depth, stall policy, RVFI ordering, or CoreMark cycle count.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n