{"type":"text","timestamp":1778604620039,"sessionID":"ses_1e2e9e624ffeMuVTTLP8WWiuAe","part":{"id":"prt_e1d18b79b001J74ryZ5sSpd6j9","messageID":"msg_e1d168bd50019H3fe2rmUaq7ZF","sessionID":"ses_1e2e9e624ffeMuVTTLP8WWiuAe","type":"text","text":"The most defensible unused `micro_opt` angle is a localized EX branch-compare cleanup: prior wins were Fmax-driven, while predictors/bypasses/extra metadata mostly lost to added muxing and routing. I’ll write a hypothesis that keeps IPC and pipeline state unchanged and only reduces duplicate signed/unsigned compare logic in `ex_stage.sv`.","time":{"start":1778604619675,"end":1778604620039},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0289aa959baf5f36016a035a4b80d48197b8b2070ae746d69a","phase":"commentary"}}}}
