{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778604641682,"sessionID":"ses_1e2e9e624ffeMuVTTLP8WWiuAe","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_uNSrvuUtM6hdTeIuPpoy54Qt","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r7s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r7s0\n+title: \"Share branch compare flags\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  Recent successful bench-core changes improved fitness by shortening hot FPGA\n+  timing paths without adding new prediction, buffering, or bypass machinery.\n+  The EX stage still builds branch decisions with separate equality, signed,\n+  and unsigned comparisons selected by branch_op. CoreMark is branch-heavy, and\n+  a taken branch redirect path must resolve in the same cycle as the ALU path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Replace the per-branch comparison expressions in rtl/ex_stage.sv with shared\n+  compare flags: one equality check, one unsigned less-than flag, and a small\n+  sign-bit correction for signed less-than. BEQ/BNE and BGE/BGEU can use these\n+  flags and inversions instead of independent signed/unsigned comparator cones.\n+  This keeps the five-stage pipeline, redirect timing, load-use policy, RVFI\n+  ordering, and CoreMark cycle count unchanged while giving synthesis a smaller\n+  EX branch-condition mux network and potentially improving Fmax.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute shared branch comparison flags and use them for all BRANCH funct3 cases, preserving existing redirect and misalignment semantics.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r7s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r7s0.yaml\n=================================