{"type":"text","timestamp":1778610674845,"sessionID":"ses_1e28cc7b7ffeS1mz7JlcsJT9nk","part":{"id":"prt_e1d751b550016bTpLhLR9VYPBF","messageID":"msg_e1d74d156001vN2K6W3345t0pC","sessionID":"ses_1e28cc7b7ffeS1mz7JlcsJT9nk","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a structural hypothesis for a one-entry posted store buffer: it targets random dmem store stalls without adding IF next-PC prediction logic or load-use bypass muxes.","time":{"start":1778610674517,"end":1778610674844},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_079c2f881990c441016a0371f267088195b0fb8220cf499f18","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778610693559,"sessionID":"ses_1e28cc7b7ffeS1mz7JlcsJT9nk","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_Iok5nYy7V6GMkr6y6HPFMkeb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r10s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r10s1\n+title: \"Posted store buffer\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current pipeline freezes all stages whenever a store reaches MEM while\n+  io_dmemReady is low, even though the store has no register result and many\n+  following CoreMark instructions are independent integer work. Prior\n+  structural attempts that added frontend prediction or load-use bypassing\n+  paid too much timing cost, but store-side decoupling can target dStall IPC\n+  loss with only local MEM/hazard changes and no IF next-PC cone growth.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry posted store buffer at the MEM stage. When a store is in\n+  EX/MEM and dmem is not ready, capture its address, replicated write data,\n+  mask, and RVFI memory fields, allow the store to retire once into MEM/WB,\n+  and let younger non-memory instructions continue while the buffer drains to\n+  the external dmem port. Stall subsequent loads or stores until the buffered\n+  store has been accepted, preserving in-order memory semantics without a\n+  load-forwarding network. This should hide a meaningful fraction of random\n+  store dStall cycles in CoreMark while keeping the nret=1 RVFI retirement\n+  contract unchanged and avoiding the frontend timing penalties that hurt\n+  earlier predictor/buffer experiments.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add minimal store-buffer metadata fields or helper typedefs if needed, without changing the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Implement a one-entry posted store buffer that captures stalled stores, drains them to dmem, and emits exactly one MEM/WB retirement for the original store.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Replace full-pipeline dmem stalls for stores with store-buffer backpressure, while still stalling loads and memory ops behind a pending buffered store.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire store-buffer pending/full status between MEM and hazard control while preserving existing imem/dmem and RVFI channel-0 ports.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r10s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r10s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r10s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r10s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,33 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r10s1\n+title: \"Posted store buffer\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current pipeline freezes all stages whenever a store reaches MEM while\n+  io_dmemReady is low, even though the store has no register result and many\n+  following CoreMark instructions are independent integer work. Prior\n+  structural attempts that added frontend prediction or load-use bypassing\n+  paid too much timing cost, but store-side decoupling can target dStall IPC\n+  loss with only local MEM/hazard changes and no IF next-PC cone growth.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry posted store buffer at the MEM stage. When a store is in\n+  EX/MEM and dmem is not ready, capture its address, replicated write data,\n+  mask, and RVFI memory fields, allow the store to retire once into MEM/WB,\n+  and let younger non-memory instructions continue while the buffer drains to\n+  the external dmem port. Stall subsequent loads or stores until the buffered\n+  store has been accepted, preserving in-order memory semantics without a\n+  load-forwarding network. This should hide a meaningful fraction of random\n+  store dStall cycles in CoreMark while keeping the nret=1 RVFI retirement\n+  contract unchanged and avoiding the frontend timing penalties that hurt\n+  earlier predictor/buffer experiments.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add minimal store-buffer metadata fields or helper typedefs if needed, without changing the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Implement a one-entry posted store buffer that captures stalled stores, drains them to dmem, and emits exactly one MEM/WB retirement for the original store.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Replace full-pipeline dmem stalls for stores with store-buffer backpressure, while still stalling loads and memory ops behind a pending buffered store.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire store-buffer pending/full status between MEM and hazard control while preserving existing imem/dmem and RVFI channel-0 ports.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r10s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r10s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r10s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r10s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r10s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,33 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r10s1\n+title: \"Posted store buffer\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current pipeline freezes all stages whenever a store reaches MEM while\n+  io_dmemReady is low, even though the store has no register result and many\n+  following CoreMark instructions are independent integer work. Prior\n+  structural attempts that added frontend prediction or load-use bypassing\n+  paid too much timing cost, but store-side decoupling can target dStall IPC\n+  loss with only local MEM/hazard changes and no IF next-PC cone growth.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry posted store buffer at the MEM stage. When a store is in\n+  EX/MEM and dmem is not ready, capture its address, replicated write data,\n+  mask, and RVFI memory fields, allow the store to retire once into MEM/WB,\n+  and let younger non-memory instructions continue while the buffer drains to\n+  the external dmem port. Stall subsequent loads or stores until the buffered\n+  store has been accepted, preserving in-order memory semantics without a\n+  load-forwarding network. This should hide a meaningful fraction of random\n+  store dStall cycles in CoreMark while keeping the nret=1 RVFI retirement\n+  contract unchanged and avoiding the frontend timing penalties that hurt\n+  earlier predictor/buffer experiments.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add minimal store-buffer metadata fields or helper typedefs if needed, without changing the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Implement a one-entry posted store buffer that captures stalled stores, drains them to dmem, and emits exactly one MEM/WB retirement for the original store.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Replace full-pipeline dmem stalls for stores with store-buffer backpressure, while still stalling loads and memory ops behind a pending buffered store.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire store-buffer pending/full status between MEM and hazard control while preserving existing imem/dmem and RVFI channel-0 ports.\"\n","additions":33,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r10s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778610693556,"end":1778610693559}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_079c2f881990c441016a0371f2b8588195b0610ade904ec29c"}},"id":"prt_e1d751c9d001VB6E6fOA7OfoAw","sessionID":"ses_1e28cc7b7ffeS1mz7JlcsJT9nk","messageID":"msg_e1d74d156001vN2K6W3345t0pC"}}
