{"type":"text","timestamp":1778612832141,"sessionID":"ses_1e26ef182ffeQSZ2E340U1c01b","part":{"id":"prt_e1d96070e001dIC1ZpkOffTEFR","messageID":"msg_e1d9364a8001IO4LjTgP792K6e","sessionID":"ses_1e26ef182ffeQSZ2E340U1c01b","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a localized structural hypothesis: split the MEM/WB forwarding hold state away from the wide RVFI retirement register so dmem stalls do not fan out a hold-enable across hundreds of MEM/WB bits.","time":{"start":1778612832014,"end":1778612832140},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0821efe56b70e319016a037a5fdba48195ab55554d1bc6fe54","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778612848792,"sessionID":"ses_1e26ef182ffeQSZ2E340U1c01b","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_1X6cyBOcle6s0RHkj83cRqQA","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r11s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r11s1\n+title: \"Split WB forwarding shadow\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior structural wins came from removing hot-path logic without adding new\n+  frontend prediction or memory-order machinery. The current MEM/WB register\n+  retains every RVFI and datapath field during a dmem stall solely so a held\n+  dependent instruction can keep seeing the previous WB forwarding value. That\n+  makes hold_mem_wb fan out across a wide retirement bundle even though only\n+  the WB forwarding data must survive the stall.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Replace the wide MEM/WB hold behavior with a narrow forwarding shadow for the\n+  WB value used by EX-stage MEM/WB forwarding. During dmem stalls, MEM/WB can\n+  continue capturing a valid-cleared bubble from the held EX/MEM load/store,\n+  while a small shadow register preserves the previous wb_w_data for any held\n+  dependent instruction whose ID/EX forwarding select is FWD_MEM_WB. This keeps\n+  RVFI retirement precise, avoids double writes, preserves the existing load-use\n+  and dmem-stall semantics, and should reduce high-fanout hold routing around\n+  the wide MEM/WB/RVFI bundle for a modest Fmax-driven gain.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Add a narrow WB-forwarding shadow register and feed EX with the shadowed value only while MEM/WB is valid-cleared for a dmem stall.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Change dmem-stall handling so MEM/WB no longer retains all data fields; it captures the current held memory payload with valid cleared.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r11s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r11s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r11s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r11s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,27 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r11s1\n+title: \"Split WB forwarding shadow\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior structural wins came from removing hot-path logic without adding new\n+  frontend prediction or memory-order machinery. The current MEM/WB register\n+  retains every RVFI and datapath field during a dmem stall solely so a held\n+  dependent instruction can keep seeing the previous WB forwarding value. That\n+  makes hold_mem_wb fan out across a wide retirement bundle even though only\n+  the WB forwarding data must survive the stall.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Replace the wide MEM/WB hold behavior with a narrow forwarding shadow for the\n+  WB value used by EX-stage MEM/WB forwarding. During dmem stalls, MEM/WB can\n+  continue capturing a valid-cleared bubble from the held EX/MEM load/store,\n+  while a small shadow register preserves the previous wb_w_data for any held\n+  dependent instruction whose ID/EX forwarding select is FWD_MEM_WB. This keeps\n+  RVFI retirement precise, avoids double writes, preserves the existing load-use\n+  and dmem-stall semantics, and should reduce high-fanout hold routing around\n+  the wide MEM/WB/RVFI bundle for a modest Fmax-driven gain.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: 