{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778612864452,"sessionID":"ses_1e26ef182ffeQSZ2E340U1c01b","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_CM6yWxB7tccdejWm5YQaJEmz","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r11s1.yaml","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r11s1.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: hyp-20260512-002-r11s1\n2: title: \"Split WB forwarding shadow\"\n3: category: structural\n4: motivation: |\n5:   Prior structural wins came from removing hot-path logic without adding new\n6:   frontend prediction or memory-order machinery. The current MEM/WB register\n7:   retains every RVFI and datapath field during a dmem stall solely so a held\n8:   dependent instruction can keep seeing the previous WB forwarding value. That\n9:   makes hold_mem_wb fan out across a wide retirement bundle even though only\n10:   the WB forwarding data must survive the stall.\n11: hypothesis: |\n12:   Replace the wide MEM/WB hold behavior with a narrow forwarding shadow for the\n13:   WB value used by EX-stage MEM/WB forwarding. During dmem stalls, MEM/WB can\n14:   continue capturing a valid-cleared bubble from the held EX/MEM load/store,\n15:   while a small shadow register preserves the previous wb_w_data for any held\n16:   dependent instruction whose ID/EX forwarding select is FWD_MEM_WB. This keeps\n17:   RVFI retirement precise, avoids double writes, preserves the existing load-use\n18:   and dmem-stall semantics, and should reduce high-fanout hold routing around\n19:   the wide MEM/WB/RVFI bundle for a modest Fmax-driven gain.\n20: expected_impact:\n21:   fitness_delta_pct: 2\n22:   confidence: medium\n23: changes:\n24:   - file: rtl/core.sv\n25:     description: \"Add a narrow WB-forwarding shadow register and feed EX with the shadowed value only while MEM/WB is valid-cleared for a dmem stall.\"\n26:   - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n27:     description: \"Change dmem-stall handling so MEM/WB no longer retains all data fields; it captures the current held memory payload with valid cleared.\"\n\n(End of file - total 27 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260512-002-r11s1\ntitle: \"Split WB forwarding shadow\"\ncategory: structural\nmotivation: |\n  Prior structural wins came from removing hot-path logic without adding new\n  frontend prediction or memory-order machinery. The current MEM/WB register\n  retains every RVFI and datapath field during a dmem stall solely so a held\n  dependent instruction can keep seeing the previous WB forwarding value. That\n  makes hold_mem_wb fan out across a wide retirement bundle even though only\n  the WB forwarding data must survive the stall.\nhypothesis: |\n  Replace the wide MEM/WB hold behavior with a narrow forwarding shadow for the\n  WB value used by EX-stage MEM/WB forwarding. During dmem stalls, MEM/WB can\n  continue capturing a valid-cleared bubble from the held EX/MEM load/store,\n  while a small shadow register preserves the previous wb_w_data for any held\n  dependent instruction whose ID/EX forwarding select is FWD_MEM_WB. This keeps\n  RVFI retirement precise, avoids double writes, preserves the existing load-use\n  and dmem-stall semantics, and should reduce high-fanout hold routing around\n  the wide MEM/WB/RVFI bundle for a modest Fmax-driven gain.\nexpected_impact:","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r11s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778612864444,"end":1778612864452}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0aaa0af07a6c3b8b016a037a7ed4c481908b2b6516b61ef5ee"}},"id":"prt_e1d9680000017DJjbJnF0oYCEm","sessionID":"ses_1e26ef182ffeQSZ2E340U1c01b","messageID":"msg_e1d96493e001go0hwS9mkU1mi3"}}
