{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1778614788455,"sessionID":"ses_1e24c8324ffeUcOZd6sitOsUPw","part":{"id":"prt_e1db3e166001gVxA8TTGBzNQ0x","messageID":"msg_e1db3dd77001qBBza4EOLxQ7mD","sessionID":"ses_1e24c8324ffeUcOZd6sitOsUPw","snapshot":"1eeb31a4d80017e8f4a8ebde87136b19da09da67","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1778614996950,"sessionID":"ses_1e24c8324ffeUcOZd6sitOsUPw","part":{"id":"prt_e1db7094b0012qDOcS7DR340Xr","messageID":"msg_e1db3dd77001qBBza4EOLxQ7mD","sessionID":"ses_1e24c8324ffeUcOZd6sitOsUPw","type":"text","text":"Prior structural wins were mostly from removing or retiming EX-path logic; recent regressions came from adding frontend prediction, memory decoupling, or extra forwarding muxes. I’m writing a narrow structural retiming hypothesis that predecodes M-extension dispatch flags in ID, keeping the existing isolated MUL and slow-unit structure intact.","time":{"start":1778614995275,"end":1778614996949},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0aa3d60444d88049016a0382d321ac8197bc588456d575cbbe","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778615016950,"sessionID":"ses_1e24c8324ffeUcOZd6sitOsUPw","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_oTDKhFWezLgMx5L9onGtyTz8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r12s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r12s1\n+title: \"Predecode M dispatch flags\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The best structural gains for this core came from keeping RV32M arithmetic\n+  off the common EX path and from registering forwarding decisions before EX.\n+  The current EX stage still re-decodes the registered ALU op every cycle to\n+  classify low-half MUL versus slow MULH/DIV/REM work, and those compare\n+  results feed the EX stall, start, ready, and result-select cones. A small\n+  ID-stage retime can shorten that control path without changing CoreMark IPC\n+  or adding predictor, memory, or bypass machinery that has regressed before.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add registered M-dispatch metadata to the ID/EX payload: one flag for\n+  ALU_MUL and one flag for the slow high-half/DIV/REM RV32M group, computed\n+  once in decode from the already-decoded alu_op and valid legality context.\n+  EX should use these registered flags for mul_start, m_start, ex_slow_busy,\n+  result_ready, operand latching, and the M-result select, while preserving\n+  the separate one-cycle mul_unit and the existing multi-cycle m_unit. This\n+  follows the proven pattern of moving small compare/priority decisions out\n+  of the EX cone, avoids reconnecting MUL to the slow shared unit, and should\n+  provide a modest Fmax-driven fitness gain with no intentional cycle-count\n+  change.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add registered ID/EX M-dispatch flags for low-half MUL and the slow RV32M operation group without changing the nret=1 RVFI interface.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute the M-dispatch flags from the decoded ALU op and latch them with the instruction in the ID/EX register.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace live ALU-op equality/case classification for M dispatch with the registered flags while keeping the existing mul_unit and m_unit behavior.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r12s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r12s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r12s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r12s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,32 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r12s1\n+title: \"Predecode M dispatch flags\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The best structural gains for this core came from keeping RV32M arithmetic\n+  off the common EX path and from registering forwarding decisions before EX.\n+  The current EX stage still re-decodes the registered ALU op every cycle to\n+  classify low-half MUL versus slow MULH/DIV/REM work, and those compare\n+  results feed the EX stall, start, ready, and result-select cones. A small\n+  ID-stage retime can shorten that control path without changing CoreMark IPC\n+  or adding predictor, memory, or bypass machinery that has regressed before.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add registered M-dispatch metadata to the ID/EX payload: one flag for\n+  ALU_MUL and one flag for the slow high-half/DIV/REM RV32M group, computed\n+  once in decode from the already-decoded alu_op and valid legality context.\n+  EX should use these registered flags for mul_start, m_start, ex_slow_busy,\n+  result_ready, operand latching, and the M-result select, while preserving\n+  the separate one-cycle mul_unit and the existing multi-cycle m_unit. This\n+  follows the proven pattern of moving small compare/priority decisions out\n+  of the EX cone, avoids reconnecting MUL to the slow shared unit, and should\n+  provide a modest Fmax-driven fitness gain with no intentional cycle-count\n+  change.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add registered ID/EX M-dispatch flags for low-half MUL and the slow RV32M operation group without changing the nret=1 RVFI interface.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute the M-dispatch flags from the decoded ALU op and latch them with the instruction in the ID/EX register.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace live ALU-op equality/case classification for M dispatch with the registered flags while keeping the existing mul_unit and m_unit behavior.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r12s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r12s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r12s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r12s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r12s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,32 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r12s1\n+title: \"Predecode M dispatch flags\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The best structural gains for this co