(regression, +23.72%): Single-cycle RV32M datapath sharing can worsen FPGA timing because sign-select muxing, 33x33 multiply width, and quotient-derived remainder logic stay in the EX output cone despite reducing source-level arithmetic duplication.\\n2: - 2026-05-12 hyp-20260512-002-r1s1 (improvement, +30.41%): Keeping only low-half MUL on the single-cycle EX path while moving rare high-half multiply and DIV/REM ops into a stalling m_unit removes slow RV32M mux cones from CoreMark's hot path and materially improves Fmax.\\n3: - 2026-05-12 hyp-20260512-003-r1s2 (regression, +13.57%): Static backward/JAL prediction can lose more to the IF-stage next-PC critical cone (immediate decode, PC+target add, alignment muxing) than it saves in CoreMark EX redirect flushes.\\n4: - 2026-05-12 hyp-20260512-001-r2s0 (regression, -1.23%): Manual 16-bit partial-product decomposition for MUL[31:0] can regress FPGA fitness because it forces three multiplies and cross-product adders into the EX cone instead of letting synthesis trim a single inferred `a * b`.\\n5: - 2026-05-12 hyp-20260512-002-r2s1 (regression, -16.67%): Elastic IF buffering can lose on this CoreMark target when buffer valid/data/PC muxing and queue control add more frontend timing cost than random imem-stall overlap can repay.\\n6: - 2026-05-12 hyp-20260512-003-r2s2 (regression, -5.44%): EX-trained tiny BTB prediction still regressed CoreMark; even without IF target recompute, the valid/t... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1778616489952,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e2326672ffeu6SPYP8feizLrS\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e1dcdd7df001CZl8RcY3u1Docu\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"8db0f0777f27c36b1fa088ec1dbf57458f358c23\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e1dcd9a00001MBg2pCLMIEYYmM\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e2326672ffeu6SPYP8feizLrS\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":43509,\"input\":42730,\"output\":263,\"reasoning\":516,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":0}},\"cost\":0}}\n{\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1778616491249,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e2326672ffeu6SPYP8feizLrS\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e1dcddcef001X5BIIhK4UYi4Jk\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e1dcdd807001mI2UV1ug1Wqd8Z\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e2326672ffeu6SPYP8feizLrS\",\"snapshot\":\"8db0f0777f27c36b1fa088ec1dbf57458f358c23\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/.agent.hyp-20260512-003-r13s2.log","time":{"start":1778616499557,"end":1778616499567}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0fd70c60744a759c016a0388b32dec819aab8dd3c59c8dc7d3"}},"id":"prt_e1dcdfd18001CCQZLphyjo2oqm","sessionID":"ses_1e2326729ffenk899NFucRvQJZ","messageID":"msg_e1dcdd87e001BBGVBDrVYvqUam"}}
