{"type":"text","timestamp":1778617783130,"sessionID":"ses_1e21fea04ffeeXeaM6yHFemfp4","part":{"id":"prt_e1de18eae001TDFVdJE8XiBOLE","messageID":"msg_e1de044c1001yTkHCZ5wwr4bCa","sessionID":"ses_1e21fea04ffeeXeaM6yHFemfp4","type":"text","text":"Prior structural history shows the durable wins came from removing timing load from hot EX/RV32M paths; frontend prediction/buffering, MEM bypassing, store buffering, and regfile rewrites repeatedly regressed. I’m going to propose a narrow structural RVFI sidecar stage that targets FPGA wrapper timing without changing pipeline IPC or memory/branch behavior.","time":{"start":1778617781934,"end":1778617783129},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_005ac2ab2787ced2016a038db5cca88197a1d2d5c4e785eb2a","phase":"commentary"}}}}
