{"type":"text","timestamp":1778618723941,"sessionID":"ses_1e212db33ffesaB289jVrpx29K","part":{"id":"prt_e1defecb30013iFiRJ62qiPEjx","messageID":"msg_e1def91aa001yVqSdFIJ6FsEzc","sessionID":"ses_1e212db33ffesaB289jVrpx29K","type":"text","text":"I’m writing the hypothesis as a structural frontend cache/memoization change: unlike the failed small fetch buffer, it targets repeated random `imemReady` stalls on hot CoreMark instruction PCs after warmup, while leaving branch prediction and redirect timing unchanged.","time":{"start":1778618723507,"end":1778618723938},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0ecac9b5a30b9eba016a0391636354819b81850f5e7df85581","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778618733175,"sessionID":"ses_1e212db33ffesaB289jVrpx29K","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_k0Y9mvborYMUBSgkxFAMLUdc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r15s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r15s1\n+title: \"Direct-mapped IF hit cache\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior structural attempts show that this core benefits most when a change\n+  removes repeated hot-path stalls without adding branch prediction or broad\n+  bypass machinery. The failed elastic IF buffer could only overlap fetch\n+  with other stalls, so it did not directly eliminate the tournament's random\n+  imemReady bubbles. CoreMark repeatedly executes a small set of hot loop\n+  instruction PCs, making repeated instruction fetch stalls a promising target.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a small direct-mapped instruction hit cache inside the IF stage. On a\n+  tag-valid hit for the current PC, IF supplies the cached instruction and\n+  treats fetch as ready even when the external io_imemReady is low; on a miss,\n+  it preserves the current behavior, waits for io_imemReady, fills the entry,\n+  and then advances. Redirects keep the existing EX-resolved flush behavior,\n+  with no branch predictor, no target lookup, and no suppression metadata.\n+  This should recover many random imem-stall cycles in CoreMark hot loops\n+  while keeping the nret=1 RVFI contract, retirement ordering, traps, and\n+  dmem semantics unchanged.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 6\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a small reset-valid direct-mapped instruction cache keyed by PC, serve cached hits independent of external imemReady, and fill entries on ready misses while preserving redirect flushing.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire IF-stage effective fetch-ready status to the hazard unit instead of using raw io_imemReady for frontend stalls.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Treat the IF-side stall input as effective fetch readiness so cache hits do not inject imem bubbles while misses retain the existing stall/flush policy.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r15s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r15s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r15s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r15s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,30 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r15s1\n+title: \"Direct-mapped IF hit cache\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior structural attempts show that this core benefits most when a change\n+  removes repeated hot-path stalls without adding branch prediction or broad\n+  bypass machinery. The failed elastic IF buffer could only overlap fetch\n+  with other stalls, so it did not directly eliminate the tournament's random\n+  imemReady bubbles. CoreMark repeatedly executes a small set of hot loop\n+  instruction PCs, making repeated instruction fetch stalls a promising target.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a small direct-mapped instruction hit cache inside the IF stage. On a\n+  tag-valid hit for the current PC, IF supplies the cached instruction and\n+  treats fetch as ready even when the external io_imemReady is low; on a miss,\n+  it preserves the current behavior, waits for io_imemReady, fills the entry,\n+  and then advances. Redirects keep the existing EX-resolved flush behavior,\n+  with no branch predictor, no target lookup, and no suppression metadata.\n+  This should recover many random imem-stall cycles in CoreMark hot loops\n+  while keeping the nret=1 RVFI contract, retirement ordering, traps, and\n+  dmem semantics unchanged.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 6\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a small reset-valid direct-mapped instruction cache keyed by PC, serve cached hits independent of external imemReady, and fill entries on ready misses while preserving redirect flushing.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire IF-stage effective fetch-ready status to the hazard unit instead of using raw io_imemReady for frontend stalls.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Treat the IF-side stall input as effective fetch readiness so cache hits do not inject imem bubbles while misses retain the existing stall/flush policy.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r15s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r15s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r15s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r15s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r15s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,30 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r15s1\n+title: \"Direct-mapped IF hit cache\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior structural attempts show that this core benefits most when a change\n+  removes repeated hot-path stalls without adding branch prediction or broad\n+  bypass machinery. The failed elastic IF buffer could only overlap fetch\n+  with other stalls, so it did not directly eliminate the tournament's random\n+  imemReady bubbles. CoreMark repeatedly executes a small set of hot loop\n+  instruction PCs, making repeated instruction fetch stalls a promising target.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a small direct-mapped instruction hit cache inside the IF stage. On a\n+  tag-valid hit for the current PC, IF supplies the cached instruction and\n+  treats fetch as ready even when the external io_imemReady is low; on a miss,\n+  it preserves the current behavior, waits for io_imemReady, fills the entry,\n+  and then advances. Redirects keep the existing EX-resolved flush behavior,\n+  with no branch predictor, no target lookup, and no suppression metadata.\n+  This should recover many random imem-stall cycles in CoreMark hot loops\n+  while keeping the nret=1 RVFI contract, retirement ordering, traps, and\n+  dmem semantics unchanged.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 6\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a small reset-valid direct-mapped instruction cache keyed by PC, serve cached hits independent of external imemReady, and fill entries on ready misses while preserving redirect flushing.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire IF-stage effective fetch-ready status to the hazard unit instead of using raw io_imemReady for frontend stalls.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Treat the IF-side stall input as effective fetch readiness so cache hits do not inject imem bubbles while misses retain the existing stall/flush policy.\"\n","additions":30,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r15s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778618733170,"end":1778618733174}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0ecac9b5a30b9eba016a039163d83c819b86f3ad88c24d2c02"}},"id":"prt_e1defee65001dQybbJGD