{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778594904620,"sessionID":"ses_1e37e9fcaffe1w2cCmxTeho5wM","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_ng4sqJENn2h7ltyNmFpNdCl6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r1s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r1s1\n+title: \"Decouple slow RV32M ops from EX\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current EX stage routes every instruction through a fully combinational\n+  RV32IM ALU that includes parallel high-half multipliers plus DIV/REM logic.\n+  CoreMark's timed region is dominated by integer ALU, load/store, branch, and\n+  low-half MUL work, while DIV/REM and high-half multiply are either absent or\n+  rare. Keeping those slow operators on the single-cycle EX timing path likely\n+  depresses Fmax without improving CoreMark IPC.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Restructure EX into a fast single-cycle I-ALU plus a separate RV32M slow-unit.\n+  Keep ALU_MUL's low-half multiply on a one-cycle fast path for CoreMark, but\n+  move MULH/MULHSU/MULHU and DIV/REM/REMU into a shared multi-cycle unit that\n+  stalls the in-order pipeline only while those rare operations are in flight.\n+  This should remove the divider and redundant high-multiply logic from the\n+  common EX critical path, reduce LUT pressure near the current budget, and\n+  raise Fmax with minimal impact on the benchmark instruction stream.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 8\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Reduce the combinational ALU to RV32I operations plus the one-cycle MUL low-half fast path; remove DIV/REM and high-half multiply from the common result mux.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Dispatch slow RV32M operations to a separate multi-cycle unit, hold EX state until result_valid, and preserve RVFI operands/result ordering.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add an EX slow-op busy stall source so IF, ID, EX/MEM, and MEM/WB control remain in-order while the M-unit runs.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add any control/status fields needed to distinguish fast MUL from slow RV32M operations through the pipeline.\"\n+  - file: rtl/m_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Introduce a shared multi-cycle implementation for MULH/MULHSU/MULHU and DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU with RV32M-correct corner cases.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Extend or adapt M-extension tests to cover the new slow-unit interface and preserve exact RV32M bit results.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r1s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r1s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r1s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r1s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,34 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r1s1\n+title: \"Decouple slow RV32M ops from EX\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current EX stage routes every instruction through a fully combinational\n+  RV32IM ALU that includes parallel high-half multipliers plus DIV/REM logic.\n+  CoreMark's timed region is dominated by integer ALU, load/store, branch, and\n+  low-half MUL work, while DIV/REM and high-half multiply are either absent or\n+  rare. Keeping those slow operators on the single-cycle EX timing path likely\n+  depresses Fmax without improving CoreMark IPC.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Restructure EX into a fast single-cycle I-ALU plus a separate RV32M slow-unit.\n+  Keep ALU_MUL's low-half multiply on a one-cycle fast path for CoreMark, but\n+  move MULH/MULHSU/MULHU and DIV/REM/REMU into a shared multi-cycle unit that\n+  stalls the in-order pipeline only while those rare operations are in flight.\n+  This should remove the divider and redundant high-multiply logic from the\n+  common EX critical path, reduce LUT pressure near the current budget, and\n+  raise Fmax with minimal impact on the benchmark instruction stream.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 8\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Reduce the combinational ALU to RV32I operations plus the one-cycle MUL low-half fast path; remove DIV/REM and high-half multiply from the common result mux.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Dispatch slow RV32M operations to a separate multi-cycle unit, hold EX state until result_valid, and preserve RVFI operands/result ordering.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add an EX slow-op busy stall source so IF, ID, EX/MEM, and MEM/WB control remain in-order while the M-unit runs.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add any control/status fields needed to distinguish fast MUL from slow RV32M operations through the pipeline.\"\n+  - file: rtl/m_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Introduce a shared multi-cycle implementation for MULH/MULHSU/MULHU and DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU with RV32M-correct corner cases.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Extend or adapt M-extension tests to cover the new slow-unit interface and preserve exact RV32M bit results.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r1s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r1s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r1s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r1s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r1s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,34 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r1s1\n+title: \"Decouple slow RV32M ops from EX\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current EX stage routes every instruction through a fully combinational\n+  RV32IM ALU that includes parallel high-half multipliers plus DIV/REM logic.\n+  CoreMark's timed region is dominated by integer ALU, load/store, branch, and\n+  low-half MUL work, while DIV/REM and high-half multiply are either absent or\n+  rare. Keeping those slow operators on the single-cycle EX timing path likely\n+  depresses Fmax without improving CoreMark IPC.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Restructure EX into a fast single-cycle I-ALU plus a separate RV32M slow-unit.\n+  Keep ALU_MUL's low-half multiply on a one-cycle fast path for CoreMark, but\n+  move MULH/MULHSU/MULHU and DIV/REM/REMU into a shared multi-cycle unit that\n+  stalls the in-order pipeline only while those rare operations are in flight.\n+  This should remove the divider and redundant high-multiply logic from the\n+  common EX critical path, reduce LUT pressure near the current budget, and\n+  raise Fmax with minimal impact on the benchmark instruction stream.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 8\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Reduce the combinational ALU to RV32I operations plus the one-cycle MUL low-half fast path; remove DIV/REM and high-half multiply from the common result mux.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Dispatch slow RV32M operations to a separate multi-cycle unit, hold EX state until result_valid, and preserve RVFI operands/result ordering.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add an EX slow-op busy stall source so IF, ID, EX/MEM, and MEM/WB control remain in-order while the M-unit runs.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add any control/status fields needed to distinguish fast MUL from slow RV32M operations through the pipeline.\"\n+  - file: rtl/m_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Introduce a shared multi-cycle implementation for MULH/MULHSU/MULHU and DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU with RV32M-correct corner cases.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Extend or adapt M-extension tests to cover the new slow-unit interface and preserve exact RV32M bit results.\"\n","additions":34,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r1s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778594904614,"end":1778594904619}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0974ac57ab926b87016a03344160448195990ab3a21b11c1ac"}},"id":"prt_e1c841fb3001P06K0wHrjw9qUG","sessionID":"ses_1e37e9fcaffe1w2cCmxTeho5wM","messageID":"msg_e1c8200cb0014zfywqbrIiAbcO"}}
