{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778596682640,"sessionID":"ses_1e36293dbffeWbhay8KPjGOAwi","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_DvDG0Sw2W7y2ZCZ8WukD4rFi","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl","offset":1,"limit":20},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\"id\": \"baseline-bench-4c67411\", \"title\": \"Baseline retest for cores/bench\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"outcome\": \"improvement\", \"fitness\": 282.82, \"delta_pct\": 0.0, \"vs_baseline\": 0.0, \"fmax_mhz\": 127.03, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4491485, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 9563, \"ff\": 1866, \"seeds\": [128.72, 127.03, 123.02], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-12T14:04:32.561624Z\", \"round_id\": 0, \"slot\": 0}\n2: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260512-001-r1s0\", \"title\": \"Share RV32M ALU datapaths\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"motivation\": \"The bench core's EX ALU currently computes three 64-bit products plus\\nindependent signed/unsigned divide and remainder expressions before selecting\\none result. Even when CoreMark mostly exercises simple ALU and MUL paths,\\nthose wide arithmetic blocks remain in the EX output cone and add LUT and\\nrouting pressure on the Tang Nano 20K. Reducing redundant arithmetic should\\nimprove median Fmax without adding cycles to the common MUL path.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The bench core's EX ALU currently computes three 64-bit products plus\\nindependent signed/unsigned divide and remainder expressions before selecting\\none result. Even when CoreMark mostly exercises simple ALU and MUL paths,\\nthose wide arithmetic blocks remain in the EX output cone and add LUT and\\nrouting pressure on the Tang Nano 20K. Reducing redundant arithmetic should\\nimprove median Fmax without adding cycles to the common MUL path.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Rewrite the real RV32M branch of rtl/alu.sv so all multiply variants use one\\nsign-configurable 33x33 product, and all DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU variants share\\nnormalized unsigned quotient/remainder logic with the existing RISC-V\\ndivide-by-zero and overflow fixups. Keep the RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS substitutions\\nequivalent and preserve single-cycle ALU latency, so CoreMark IPC should not\\nregress while the FPGA critical path and LUT/routing pressure improve.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 5, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\", \"description\": \"Replace parallel RV32M multiply/divide expressions with shared sign-normalized combinational datapaths while preserving ALTOPS and RV32M corner-case semantics.\"}, {\"file\": \"test/test_alu.py\", \"description\": \"Add or retain focused RV32M corner vectors for MULH/MULHSU/MULHU and DIV/REM divide-by-zero/overflow cases to guard the shared datapath rewrite.\"}]}, \"expected_impact... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n3: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260512-002-r1s1\", \"title\": \"Decouple slow RV32M ops from EX\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"motivation\": \"The current EX stage routes every instruction through a fully combinational\\nRV32IM ALU that includes parallel high-half multipliers plus DIV/REM logic.\\nCoreMark's timed region is dominated by integer ALU, load/store, branch, and\\nlow-half MUL work, while DIV/REM and high-half multiply are either absent or\\nrare. Keeping those slow operators on the single-cycle EX timing path likely\\ndepresses Fmax without improving CoreMark IPC.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current EX stage routes every instruction through a fully combinational\\nRV32IM ALU that includes parallel high-half multipliers plus DIV/REM logic.\\nCoreMark's timed region is dominated by integer ALU, load/store, branch, and\\nlow-half MUL work, while DIV/REM and high-half multiply are either absent or\\nrare. Keeping those slow operators on the single-cycle EX timing path likely\\ndepresses Fmax without improving CoreMark IPC.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Restructure EX into a fast single-cycle I-ALU plus a separate RV32M slow-unit.\\nKeep ALU_MUL's low-half multiply on a one-cycle fast path for CoreMark, but\\nmove MULH/MULHSU/MULHU and DIV/REM/REMU into a shared multi-cycle unit that\\nstalls the in-order pipeline only while those rare operations are in flight.\\nThis should remove the divider and redundant high-multiply logic from the\\ncommon EX critical path, reduce LUT pressure near the current budget, and\\nraise Fmax with minimal impact on the benchmark instruction stream.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 8, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\", \"description\": \"Reduce the combinational ALU to RV32I operations plus the one-cycle MUL low-half fast path; remove DIV/REM and high-half multiply from the common result mux.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Dispatch slow RV32M operations to a separate multi-cycle unit, hold EX state until result_valid, and ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n4: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260512-003-r1s2\", \"title\": \"Static backward-branch next-PC predictor\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"motivation\": \"The current five-stage core resolves all branches and jumps in EX, so every\\ntaken loop branch or direct jump pays the redirect flush penalty. CoreMark is\\nloop-heavy, and a low-cost predictor that fetches backward branch targets and\\ndirect JAL targets immediately should recover cycles without adding large FPGA\\nstructures or touching the single-retire RVFI contract.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current five-stage core resolves all branches and jumps in EX, so every\\ntaken loop branch or direct jump pays the redirect flush penalty. CoreMark is\\nloop-heavy, and a low-cost predictor that fetches backward branch targets and\\ndirect JAL targets immediately should recover cycles without adding large FPGA\\nstructures or touching the single-retire RVFI contract.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add an IF-stage static next-PC predictor: predict JAL taken, predict\\nconditional branches with a negative B-immediate taken, and otherwise predict\\nfall-through. Carry the predicted next PC through IF/ID and ID/EX so EX can\\nredirect only when the resolved architectural next PC differs from the\\nprediction. This should turn the common CoreMark loop-back branch from a\\ntaken-branch flush into a correct-path fetch, while forward exits still pay\\nonly the existing mispredict recovery cost.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 6, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add predicted-next-PC metadata to the IF/ID and ID/EX pipeline bundles.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Compute the static backward-branch/JAL prediction from the fetched instruction and use it for the next PC when not stalled or redirected.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Propagate IF-stage prediction metadata into the ID/EX register alongside the decoded instruction.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Compare r... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n\n(End of file - total 4 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\"id\": \"baseline-bench-4c67411\", \"title\": \"Baseline retest for cores/bench\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"outcome\": \"improvement\", \"fitness\": 282.82, \"delta_pct\": 0.0, \"vs_baseline\": 0.0, \"fmax_mhz\": 127.03, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4491485, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 9563, \"ff\": 1866, \"seeds\": [128.72, 127.03, 123.02], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-12T14:04:32.561624Z\", \"round_id\"