{"type":"text","timestamp":1778596924761,"sessionID":"ses_1e36293dbffeWbhay8KPjGOAwi","part":{"id":"prt_e1ca34bdf001n3c9CTvNwGXKMi","messageID":"msg_e1c9fd5c90016LkjZosv5TQ9SE","sessionID":"ses_1e36293dbffeWbhay8KPjGOAwi","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a structural hypothesis around a small elastic fetch/decode boundary that overlaps instruction-memory stalls with existing pipeline stalls, without changing RVFI or the memory contract.","time":{"start":1778596924383,"end":1778596924760},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0b8f275263ed5ea5016a033c3c3ab08198b5fd862f89682132","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778596948218,"sessionID":"ses_1e36293dbffeWbhay8KPjGOAwi","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_EWp3Ie37KqBx37vSUn0DmAL3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r2s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r2s1\n+title: \"Elastic IF fetch buffer\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current front end ties instruction fetch directly to decode: when ID is\n+  stalled for load-use, dmem backpressure, or a slow M operation, the PC also\n+  holds and no useful instruction fetch can be performed. With the tournament\n+  cosim injecting about 22 percent random instruction stalls, those missed\n+  opportunities turn independent stalls into serialized bubbles. The failed\n+  static predictor showed that adding next-PC computation in IF is too costly,\n+  so the better structural target is decoupling fetch from decode without\n+  adding branch-target logic to the IF critical path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Insert a tiny elastic fetch buffer between IF and ID. The buffer should keep\n+  the existing direct fall-through path when decode is ready, but when ID/EX is\n+  stalled it should let IF continue fetching sequential instructions into one\n+  or two registered slots until the buffer is full. Decode then consumes from\n+  the buffer before requesting a fresh instruction, hiding later imemReady=0\n+  cycles behind earlier load-use, dmem, or slow-M stalls. Redirects flush the\n+  buffer and restart fetch at the resolved target, preserving precise single\n+  retirement and the existing RVFI channel-0 contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add any fetch-buffer metadata needed to keep PC, instruction, and valid state stable across decode stalls.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace the purely combinational IF/ID payload with a small elastic sequential fetch buffer that can prefetch while decode is stalled and flushes on redirects.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Separate decode-empty stalls from raw imemReady stalls so ID only waits when no buffered instruction is available, while IF stalls only when the buffer is full.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the fetch-buffer ready/valid signals between IF, ID, and the hazard unit without changing the top-level IO or single-channel RVFI ports.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r2s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r2s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r2s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r2s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,33 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r2s1\n+title: \"Elastic IF fetch buffer\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current front end ties instruction fetch directly to decode: when ID is\n+  stalled for load-use, dmem backpressure, or a slow M operation, the PC also\n+  holds and no useful instruction fetch can be performed. With the tournament\n+  cosim injecting about 22 percent random instruction stalls, those missed\n+  opportunities turn independent stalls into serialized bubbles. The failed\n+  static predictor showed that adding next-PC computation in IF is too costly,\n+  so the better structural target is decoupling fetch from decode without\n+  adding branch-target logic to the IF critical path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Insert a tiny elastic fetch buffer between IF and ID. The buffer should keep\n+  the existing direct fall-through path when decode is ready, but when ID/EX is\n+  stalled it should let IF continue fetching sequential instructions into one\n+  or two registered slots until the buffer is full. Decode then consumes from\n+  the buffer before requesting a fresh instruction, hiding later imemReady=0\n+  cycles behind earlier load-use, dmem, or slow-M stalls. Redirects flush the\n+  buffer and restart fetch at the resolved target, preserving precise single\n+  retirement and the existing RVFI channel-0 contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add any fetch-buffer metadata needed to keep PC, instruction, and valid state stable across decode stalls.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace the purely combinational IF/ID payload with a small elastic sequential fetch buffer that can prefetch while decode is stalled and flushes on redirects.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Separate decode-empty stalls from raw imemReady stalls so ID only waits when no buffered instruction is available, while IF stalls only when the buffer is full.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the fetch-buffer ready/valid signals between IF, ID, and the hazard unit without changing the top-level IO or single-channel RVFI ports.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r2s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r2s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r2s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experime