{"type":"text","timestamp":1778598702620,"sessionID":"ses_1e3435392ffeBisIBxlvhvK74c","part":{"id":"prt_e1cbe65ed0014YVif3E5qJU64r","messageID":"msg_e1cbd1654001J5pZCznk4dzdkH","sessionID":"ses_1e3435392ffeBisIBxlvhvK74c","type":"text","text":"Prior structural history shows the successful path was removing rare slow RV32M logic from the common EX cone, while frontend buffering regressed. The next structural target I’m choosing is a MEM-to-EX load-use bypass, because it improves IPC without adding predictor state or IF next-PC logic.","time":{"start":1778598700525,"end":1778598702618},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_09414c4af0141f1e016a03432c649081949b7909c7d5fa0a29","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778598725781,"sessionID":"ses_1e3435392ffeBisIBxlvhvK74c","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_JIk1VitHisK8Yg96T9yYjCYS","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r3s1\n+title: \"MEM-to-EX load-use bypass\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current five-stage pipeline always inserts a bubble when an instruction\n+  consumes the destination of the immediately preceding load. That is safe but\n+  pessimistic for the zero-wait or ready dmem cycles that dominate the FPGA and\n+  random-stall CoreMark runs: the load value is already formed in MEM while the\n+  dependent instruction would be in EX. Previous frontend structural work lost\n+  too much Fmax, so the better IPC target is a local backend bypass that leaves\n+  IF next-PC timing untouched.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a MEM-stage load-data bypass into the EX operand forwarding network and\n+  change load-use hazard handling so the dependent instruction stalls only when\n+  the load is actually waiting on dmem or cannot produce a valid value. The MEM\n+  stage should expose the sign/zero-extended load result plus a valid rd tag;\n+  EX should select that value ahead of the older MEM/WB path for matching rs1 or\n+  rs2 operands. This should remove common one-cycle load-use bubbles in\n+  CoreMark while preserving the existing single-retire RVFI contract and keeping\n+  branch prediction/front-end timing unchanged.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire a MEM-stage load bypass value/tag/valid path from mem_stage into the EX forwarding network while preserving the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Expose the aligned and sign/zero-extended load result as a bypassable value only when the load is valid, aligned, and not suppressed by a trap.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a MEM-load forwarding input and operand mux selection so dependent ALU, branch, store-data, and JALR operands can consume a just-loaded value.\"\n+  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Prioritize MEM-stage load-data forwarding for EX source operands before falling back to EX/MEM ALU and MEM/WB writeback forwarding.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Relax the unconditional load-use bubble so it only stalls when the pending load cannot be bypassed, such as during dmem backpressure.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,34 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r3s1\n+title: \"MEM-to-EX load-use bypass\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current five-stage pipeline always inserts a bubble when an instruction\n+  consumes the destination of the immediately preceding load. That is safe but\n+  pessimistic for the zero-wait or ready dmem cycles that dominate the FPGA and\n+  random-stall CoreMark runs: the load value is already formed in MEM while the\n+  dependent instruction would be in EX. Previous frontend structural work lost\n+  too much Fmax, so the better IPC target is a local backend bypass that leaves\n+  IF next-PC timing untouched.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a MEM-stage load-data bypass into the EX operand forwarding network and\n+  change load-use hazard handling so the dependent instruction stalls only when\n+  the load is actually waiting on dmem or cannot produce a valid value. The MEM\n+  stage should expose the sign/zero-extended load result plus a valid rd tag;\n+  EX should select that value ahead of the older MEM/WB path for matching rs1 or\n+  rs2 operands. This should remove common one-cycle load-use bubbles in\n+  CoreMark while preserving the existing single-retire RVFI contract and keeping\n+  branch prediction/front-end timing unchanged.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire a MEM-stage load bypass value/tag/valid path from mem_stage into the EX forwarding network while preserving the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Expose the aligned and sign/zero-extended load result as a bypassable value only when the load is valid, aligned, and not suppressed by a trap.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a MEM-load forwarding input and operand mux selection so dependent ALU, branch, store-data, and JALR operands can consume a just-loaded value.\"\n+  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Prioritize MEM-stage load-data forwarding for EX source operands before falling back to EX/MEM ALU and MEM/WB writeback forwarding.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Relax the unconditional load-use bubble so it only stalls when the pending load cannot be bypassed, such as during dmem backpressure.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,34 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r3s1\n+title: \"MEM-to-EX load-use bypass\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current five-stage pipeline always inserts a bubble when an instruction\n+  consumes the destination of the immediately preceding load. That is safe but\n+  pessimistic for the zero-wait or ready dmem cycles that dominate the FPGA and\n+  random-stall CoreMark runs: the load value is already formed in MEM while the\n+  dependent instruction would be in EX. Previous frontend structural work lost\n+  too much Fmax, so the better IPC target is a local backend bypass that leaves\n+  IF next-PC timing untouched.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a MEM-stage load-data bypass into the EX operand forwarding network and\n+  change load-use hazard handling so the dependent instruction stalls only when\n+  the load is actually waiting on dmem or cannot produce a valid value. The MEM\n+  stage should expose the sign/zero-extended load result plus a valid rd tag;\n+  EX should select that value ahead of the older MEM/WB path for matching rs1 or\n+  rs2 operands. This should remove common one-cycle load-use bubbles in\n+  CoreMark while preserving the existing single-retire RVFI contract and keeping\n+  branch prediction/front-end timing unchanged.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire a MEM-stage load bypass value/tag/valid path from mem_stage into the EX forwarding network while preserving the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Expose the aligned and sign/zero-extended load result as a bypassable value only when the load is valid, aligned, and not suppressed by a trap.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a MEM-load forwarding input and operand mux selection so dependent ALU, branch, store-data, and JALR operands can consume a just-loaded value.\"\n+  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Prioritize MEM-stage load-data forwarding for EX source operands before falling back to EX/MEM ALU and MEM/WB writeback forwarding.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Relax the unconditional load-use bubble so it only stalls when the pending load cannot be bypassed, such as during dmem backpressure.\"\n","additions":34,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778598725777,"end":1778598725780}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09414c4af0141f1e016a03432e89208194b064fc37355fd9d4"}},"id":"prt_e1cbe6e1c001W4vwx92l8wnNM2","sessionID":"ses_1e3435392ffeBisIBxlvhvK74c","messageID":"msg_e1cbd1654001J5pZCznk4dzdkH"}}
