{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778600244006,"sessionID":"ses_1e32f18c1ffew470Q77k907r3C","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_KF84LNw84Q6lHdrjN3l8Q03b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r4s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r4s1\n+title: \"Register forwarding selects\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  Recent structural IPC attempts added frontend/backend muxing and lost more Fmax than they recovered in cycles. The remaining attractive structural target is the EX operand path itself: live rd/rs compare and priority-select logic currently feeds the ALU and low-half MUL muxes every cycle. Retiming those decisions into the ID/EX register should shorten the hot EX cone without changing branch prediction, load-use behavior, or the nret=1 RVFI contract.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Compute the forwarding source for the instruction while it is still in decode, then carry two registered forwarding-select fields in id_ex_t. Decode can compare the IF/ID rs addresses against the current ID/EX producer, which will be EX/MEM next cycle, and the current EX/MEM producer, which will be MEM/WB next cycle. The existing load-use bubble remains in place, so a load immediately ahead is not treated as an EX/MEM-forwardable producer. EX then uses only the registered select bits plus the existing forwarded data buses, removing the live comparator/priority network from the ALU and one-cycle MUL timing path while preserving identical IPC and stall semantics.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add rs1/rs2 forwarding-select fields to the ID/EX pipeline bundle so forwarding decisions are registered with the instruction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Retarget forwarding selection to decode-time producer tags: IF/ID rs versus current ID/EX and EX/MEM writers, with EX/MEM priority only for non-load producers that will have a valid ALU result next cycle.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Accept decode-time forwarding-select inputs and latch them into ID/EX alongside operands, clearing them on flush/bubble.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Remove live forwarding-select inputs and drive the operand muxes from the registered ID/EX forwarding-select fields.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Rewire the forwarding unit around IF/ID decode sources and current producer metadata while preserving existing hazard, stall, and RVFI retirement behavior.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r4s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r4s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r4s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r4s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,21 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r4s1\n+title: \"Register forwarding selects\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  Recent structural IPC attempts added frontend/backend muxing and lost more Fmax than they recovered in cycles. The remaining attractive structural target is the EX operand path itself: live rd/rs compare and priority-select logic currently feeds the ALU and low-half MUL muxes every cycle. Retiming those decisions into the ID/EX register should shorten the hot EX cone without changing branch prediction, load-use behavior, or the nret=1 RVFI contract.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Compute the forwarding source for the instruction while it is still in decode, then carry two