{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778601619447,"sessionID":"ses_1e3175243ffehaPV1OwgL5rM1c","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_17hXshnvIv8Ij7lmaGekQKOT","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r5s1.yaml","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r5s1.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: hyp-20260512-002-r5s1\n2: title: \"Register WB forwarding data\"\n3: category: structural\n4: motivation: |\n5:   The r4 structural win registered forwarding selects, which suggests the EX\n6:   operand cone is still timing-sensitive after the slow RV32M work was moved\n7:   off the common path. MEM/WB forwarding still feeds EX through the live WB\n8:   write-data mux, so a dependent instruction forwarded from WB carries\n9:   mem_to_reg selection into the EX operand mux, ALU, and one-cycle MUL path.\n10:   That mux is small, but it sits on the hottest every-cycle datapath and does\n11:   not buy CoreMark any IPC.\n12: hypothesis: |\n13:   Add a registered final writeback value at the MEM/WB boundary and use it for\n14:   the regfile write port, RVFI rd_wdata, and MEM/WB-to-EX forwarding. MEM still\n15:   computes load extension and ALU-vs-load selection before the MEM/WB flop; EX\n16:   then sees only a registered 32-bit forwarding value rather than the live\n17:   WB-stage result mux. This preserves the five-stage retirement point, load-use\n18:   bubble policy, dmem hold semantics, and nret=1 RVFI contract while shortening\n19:   the post-r4 EX operand path with no intentional cycle-count change.\n20: expected_impact:\n21:   fitness_delta_pct: 2\n22:   confidence: medium\n23: changes:\n24:   - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n25:     description: \"Add a final writeback-data field to mem_wb_t so the MEM/WB boundary carries the value used for writes and forwarding.\"\n26:   - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n27:     description: \"Compute and register the final WB data alongside existing read_data and alu_result fields, retaining it across hold_wb stalls.\"\n28:   - file: rtl/wb_stage.sv\n29:     description: \"Drive w_data from the registered MEM/WB value instead of recomputing the mem_to_reg mux in the WB-stage combinational path.\"\n\n(End of file - total 29 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260512-002-r5s1\ntitle: \"Register WB forwarding data\"\ncategory: structural\nmotivation: |\n  The r4 structural win registered forwarding selects, which suggests the EX\n  operand cone is still timing-sensitive after the slow RV32M work was moved\n  off the common path. MEM/WB forwarding still feeds EX through the live WB\n  write-data mux, so a dependent instruction forwarded from WB carries\n  mem_to_reg selection into the EX operand mux, ALU, and one-cycle MUL path.\n  That mux is small, but it sits on the hottest every-cycle datapath and does\n  not buy CoreMark any IPC.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a registered final writeback value at the MEM/WB boundary and use it for\n  the regfile write port, RVFI rd_wdata, and MEM/WB-to-EX forwarding. MEM still\n  computes load extension and ALU-vs-load selection before the MEM/WB flop; EX\n  then sees only a registered 32-bit forwarding value rather than the live\n  WB-stage result mux. This preserves the five-stage retirement point, load-use\n  bubble policy, dmem hold semantics, and nret=1 RVFI contract while shortening\n  the post-r4 EX operand path with no intentional cycle-count change.\nexpected_impact:","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r5s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778601619440,"end":1778601619445}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d2926865bb338a0016a034e9355608196b668b90aae0bf99f"}},"id":"prt_e1ceaefe8001s6E1pj5PEe7n4f","sessionID":"ses_1e3175243ffehaPV1OwgL5rM1c","messageID":"msg_e1ceab4da002oD212y9Kt3P0q4"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778601619491,"sessionID":"ses_1e3175243ffehaPV1OwgL5rM1c","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_7mccmpWt7M1LX7nrpcLi6tgn","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/schemas/hypothesis.schema.json","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/schemas/hypothesis.schema.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\",\n3:   \"type\": \"object\",\n4:   \"required\": [\"id\",\"title\",\"category\",\"motivation\",\"hypothesis\",\"expected_impact\",\"changes\"],\n5:   \"properties\": {\n6:     \"id\":       {\"type\": \"string\", \"pattern\": \"^hyp-[0-9]{8}-[0-9]{3}(-r[0-9]+s[0-9]+)?$\"},\n7:     \"title\":    {\"type\": \"string\", \"minLength\": 5},\n8:     \"category\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"enum\": [\"micro_opt\",\"structural\",\"extension\",\"predictor\",\"memory\"]},\n9:     \"motivation\":  {\"type\": \"string\", \"minLength\": 20},\n10:     \"hypothesis\":  {\"type\": \"string\", \"minLength\": 20},\n11:     \"expected_impact\": {\n12:       \"type\": \"object\",\n13:       \"required\": [\"fitness_delta_pct\",\"confidence\"],\n14:       \"properties\": {\n15:         \"fitness_delta_pct\": {\"type\": \"integer\"},\n16:         \"confidence\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"enum\": [\"low\",\"medium\",\"high\"]}\n17:       }\n18:     },\n19:     \"changes\": {\n20:       \"type\": \"array\", \"minItems\": 1,\n21:       \"items\": {\n22:         \"type\": \"object\",\n23:         \"required\": [\"file\",\"description\"],\n24:         \"properties\": {\n25:           \"file\":        {\n26:             \"type\": \"string\",\n27:             \"description\": \"Must be under rtl/ (any extension) or be a test/test_*.py cocotb suite. Anything else is rejected by the runtime sandbox check.\",\n28:             \"pattern\": \"^(rtl/[^.].*|test/test_[^/]+\\\\.py)$\"\n29:           },\n30:           \"description\": {\"type\": \"string\"}\n31:         }\n32:       }\n33:     }\n34:   }\n35: }\n\n(End of file - total 35 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\",\n  \"type\": \"object\",\n  \"required\": [\"id\",\"title\",\"category\",\"motivation\",\"hypothesis\",\"expected_impact\",\"changes\"],\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"id\":       {\"type\": \"string\", \"pattern\": \"^hyp-[0-9]{8}-[0-9]{3}(-r[0-9]+s[0-9]+)?$\"},\n    \"title\":    {\"type\": \"string\", \"minLength\": 5},\n    \"category\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"enum\": [\"micro_opt\",\"structural\",\"extension\",\"predictor\",\"memory\"]},\n    \"motivation\":  {\"type\": \"string\", \"minLength\": 20},\n    \"hypothesis\":  {\"type\": \"string\", \"minLength\": 20},\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"type\": \"object\",\n      \"required\": [\"fitness_delta_pct\",\"confidence\"],\n      \"properties\": {\n        \"fitness_delta_pct\": {\"type\": \"integer\"},\n        \"confidence\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"enum\": [\"low\",\"medium\",\"high\"]}\n      }\n    },\n    \"changes\": {\n      \"type\": \"array\", \"minItems\": 1,","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"schemas/hypothesis.schema.json","time":{"start":1778601619485,"end":1778601619490}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d2926865bb338a0016a034e93556c8196b7c548174b26c630"}},"id":"prt_e1ceaeffe001PplTDQvY5UBKen","sessionID":"ses_1e3175243ffehaPV1OwgL5rM1c","messageID":"msg_e1ceab4da002oD212y9Kt3P0q4"}}
