{"type":"text","timestamp":1778603527137,"sessionID":"ses_1e2fed7abffeL4YF6oJ9GhlF0p","part":{"id":"prt_e1d0805a5001akSUMW13ibcJYI","messageID":"msg_e1d07bc1e001TRqddNy45OmfPx","sessionID":"ses_1e2fed7abffeL4YF6oJ9GhlF0p","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a low-risk structural hypothesis that removes unused pipeline sideband state instead of adding more prediction, buffering, or bypass control, since those have consistently lost timing.","time":{"start":1778603525541,"end":1778603527136},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_022ded27fd661bab016a03560571888196b5d054052f1ca0af","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778603549543,"sessionID":"ses_1e2fed7abffeL4YF6oJ9GhlF0p","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_Jhb3YNH5JluB6hvBtxNrupWn","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r6s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r6s1\n+title: \"Slim unused pipeline sidebands\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  Recent structural wins came from shortening hot pipeline cones without adding\n+  new IPC machinery, while fetch buffers, load bypasses, and predictors lost\n+  more Fmax than they recovered. The current RTL still carries some metadata\n+  that is not consumed after EX, including EX/MEM branch_taken and\n+  branch_target fields plus an is_lui control bit that is redundant with\n+  ALU_LUI. Those dead sidebands add registers, mux fanout, and routing pressure\n+  on a design where small retiming changes have already moved fitness.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Prune the unused pipeline sidebands rather than changing execution behavior:\n+  remove branch_taken and branch_target from ex_mem_t and stop registering them,\n+  and remove the dead is_lui control bit from ctrl_t while keeping LUI legality\n+  represented by ALU_LUI and the existing immediate path. Branch redirect and\n+  pc_next calculation still use local EX signals in the same cycle, so IPC,\n+  stall behavior, traps, and the nret=1 RVFI contract are unchanged. The smaller\n+  pipeline payload should reduce EX/MEM fanout, backend register count, and\n+  nextpnr routing pressure, yielding a modest Fmax-driven fitness gain.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Remove the unused is_lui control bit and dead EX/MEM branch_taken/branch_target fields from the pipeline bundle definitions.\"\n+  - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n+    description: \"Drop the redundant is_lui output while preserving LUI decode as a legal ALU_LUI immediate operation.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Stop wiring and storing the removed is_lui decode bit in ctrl_t.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Keep branch_taken and branch_target as local redirect/pc_next signals only, no longer registering unused EX/MEM sideband fields.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Clean up comments or unused-field annotations that referenced the removed EX/MEM branch sidebands.\"\n+  - file: test/test_decoder.py\n+    description: \"Update decoder unit expectations for the removed is_lui port while keeping LUI legality and ALU_LUI coverage.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r6s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r6s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r6s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r6s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,36 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r6s1\n+title: \"Slim unused pipeline sidebands\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  Recent structural wins came from shortening hot pipeline cones without adding\n+  new IPC machinery, while fetch buffers, load bypasses, and predictors lost\n+  more Fmax than they recovered. The current RTL still carries some metadata\n+  that is not consumed after EX, including EX/MEM branch_taken and\n+  branch_target fields plus an is_lui control bit that is redundant with\n+  ALU_LUI. Those dead sidebands add registers, mux fanout, and routing pressure\n+  on a design where small retiming changes have already moved fitness.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  P