{"type":"text","timestamp":1778606636597,"sessionID":"ses_1e2ca6184ffes01WuuUxF8Lsy5","part":{"id":"prt_e1d3778ff0010Re66oP3TUd0ku","messageID":"msg_e1d360067001nOG31sl6SqxfO0","sessionID":"ses_1e2ca6184ffes01WuuUxF8Lsy5","type":"text","text":"The prior structural wins point to removing hot EX datapath logic without adding frontend prediction/control. The strongest remaining structural bet is to take the low-half MUL out of the single-cycle ALU cone using a tiny registered MUL path, accepting rare MUL stalls only when the instruction stream actually uses MUL.","time":{"start":1778606635263,"end":1778606636596},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_08eb5b8ef755a03e016a03622b1d88819380e068d7815687d1","phase":"commentary"}}}}
