{"type":"text","timestamp":1778606694490,"sessionID":"ses_1e2ca6184ffes01WuuUxF8Lsy5","part":{"id":"prt_e1d385c62001yjMhLddGXbUDa0","messageID":"msg_e1d37ac13001JSVpCMWcJ2tY7z","sessionID":"ses_1e2ca6184ffes01WuuUxF8Lsy5","type":"text","text":"Writing the hypothesis file now with only `cores/bench`-scoped `rtl/...` and `test/...` paths.","time":{"start":1778606693474,"end":1778606694489},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_07e83f3ba79ae91a016a0362655c2c81908ab1d5cdf5570855","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778606717073,"sessionID":"ses_1e2ca6184ffes01WuuUxF8Lsy5","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_uwBykyxHJFxxR4e9KycZy1wg","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r8s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r8s1\n+title: \"Registered low-half MUL path\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior structural wins came from taking rare RV32M work out of the common EX\n+  result cone, while frontend predictors, fetch buffering, MEM bypassing, and\n+  regfile rewrites all lost more timing than they recovered. The remaining\n+  high-cost logic still present on every fast EX timing analysis path is the\n+  single-cycle 32x32 low-half MUL in alu.sv. CoreMark needs MUL support, but it\n+  does not execute MUL every cycle, so a small MUL-only latency penalty may be\n+  cheaper than keeping the multiplier in the ADD/load-address/branch ALU cone.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Split ALU_MUL out of the combinational fast ALU and handle it with a tiny\n+  registered low-half multiply side path in EX. Non-MUL RV32I ALU operations,\n+  branch compares, load/store address generation, JAL/JALR link values, and the\n+  existing slow high-half/DIV/REM m_unit behavior should remain unchanged. When\n+  ALU_MUL reaches EX, the pipeline holds for the registered product, then emits\n+  exactly one EX/MEM result with the original RVFI operands and order. Under\n+  RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS the side path should register the same formal substitute\n+  expression instead of the real product. This should remove the DSP/multiplier\n+  path from the common ALU output mux and improve Tang Nano Fmax enough to\n+  offset occasional MUL bubbles in CoreMark.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Remove ALU_MUL from the combinational fast ALU so ordinary ALU, branch, and address operations no longer share the multiplier result mux.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Dispatch ALU_MUL to a registered low-half multiply side path, hold ID/EX while the product is pending, and preserve single retirement plus RVFI operand stability.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mul_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add a tiny one-result registered low-half MUL unit with a matching RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS substitute path.\"\n+  - file: test/test_mul_unit.py\n+    description: \"Add focused cocotb vectors for the registered low-half MUL path, including signed-looking operands and ALTOPS-compatible reset/handshake behavior.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r8s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r8s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r8s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r8s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,34 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r8s1\n+title: \"Registered low-half MUL path\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior structural wins came from taking rare RV32M work out of the common EX\n+  result cone, while frontend predictors, fetch buffering, MEM bypassing, and\n+  regfile rewrites all lost more timing than they recovered. The remaining\n+  high-cost logic still present on every fast EX timing analysis path is the\n+  single-cycle 32x32 low-half MUL in alu.sv. CoreMark needs MUL support, but it\n+  does not execute MUL every cycle, so a small MUL-only latency penalty may be\n+  cheaper than keeping the multiplier in the ADD/load-address/branch ALU cone.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Split ALU_MUL out of the combinational fast ALU and handle it with a tiny\n+  registered low-half multiply side path in EX. Non-MUL RV32I ALU operations,\n+  branch compares, load/store address generation, JAL/JALR link values, and the\n+  existing slow high-half/DIV/REM m_unit behavior should remain unchanged. When\n+  ALU_MUL reaches EX, the pipeline holds for the registered product, then emits\n+  exactly one EX/MEM result with the original RVFI operands and order. Under\n+  RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS the side path should register the same formal substitute\n+  expression instead of the real product. This should remove the DSP/multiplier\n+  path from the common ALU output mux and improve Tang Nano Fmax enough to\n+  offset occasional MUL bubbles in CoreMark.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Remove ALU_MUL from the combinational fast ALU so ordinary ALU, branch, and address operations no longer share the multiplier result mux.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Dispatch ALU_MUL to a registered low-half multiply side path, hold ID/EX while the product is pending, and preserve single retirement plus RVFI operand stability.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mul_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add a tiny one-result registered low-half MUL unit with a matching RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS substitute path.\"\n+  - file: test/test_mul_unit.py\n+    description: \"Add focused cocotb vectors for the registered low-half MUL path, including signed-looking operands and ALTOPS-compatible reset/handshake behavior.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r8s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r8s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r8s1.y