{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778612731730,"sessionID":"ses_1e26ef0b2ffe6cCz4OUX98cXnz","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_5Osp4IaiJWkgPZbxWlUnJmA7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r11s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r11s2\n+title: \"Redirect target replay cache\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Every prior control-flow predictor on this core lost fitness because it put\n+  lookup, target-add, next-PC muxing, or prediction metadata on the normal\n+  fetch path. The existing pipeline still pays a redirect bubble for hot loop\n+  branches and direct jumps after EX has already resolved the correct target.\n+  A predictor that only acts on resolved redirects can target those bubbles\n+  without perturbing the common fall-through `pc + 4` fetch path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a tiny target-instruction replay cache in IF, filled by ordinary\n+  successful instruction fetches as `{pc, instr, pc_plus4}` entries. When EX\n+  asserts a redirect to a cached target, IF injects the cached target\n+  instruction into ID in that same cycle and advances the PC to the cached\n+  `pc_plus4`, while the hazard unit suppresses only the redirect flush that\n+  would have killed this injected instruction. Cache misses keep the existing\n+  redirect behavior exactly. This is a predictor of the target instruction,\n+  not a branch-direction predictor: there is no EX redirect suppression, no\n+  speculative wrong-path retirement, and no predictor lookup on normal\n+  fall-through fetches. Hot CoreMark loop targets should hit after warmup and\n+  save one redirect bubble with much lower timing risk than the failed IF-side\n+  branch, BTB, RAS, loop, JAL, and stall-shadow predictors.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a tiny filled-on-fetch target-instruction replay cache and use it only on resolved redirect target hits to inject the cached instruction and advance PC to cached pc+4.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add a redirect-inject input so redirect cache hits do not flush the injected target instruction, while misses and all stalls keep existing behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the IF-stage redirect-inject signal into hazard control without changing the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r11s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r11s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r11s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r11s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,33 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r11s2\n+title: \"Redirect target replay cache\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Every prior control-flow predictor on this core lost fitness because it put\n+  lookup, target-add, next-PC muxing, or prediction metadata on the normal\n+  fetch path. The existing pipeline still pays a redirect bubble for hot loop\n+  branches and direct jumps after EX has already resolved the correct target.\n+  A predictor that only acts on resolved redirects can target those bubbles\n+  without perturbing the common fall-through `pc + 4` fetch path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a tiny target-instruction replay cache in IF, filled by ordinary\n+  successful instruction fetches as `{pc, instr, pc_plus4}` entries. When EX\n+  asserts a redirect to a cached target, IF injects the cached target\n+  instruction into 