{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1778614793057,"sessionID":"ses_1e24c8305ffeFa590m6IWi1jQq","part":{"id":"prt_e1db3f35f001BCNRH1K9EhWrhI","messageID":"msg_e1db3ef0f001dl96jJDR9OM8X1","sessionID":"ses_1e24c8305ffeFa590m6IWi1jQq","snapshot":"1eeb31a4d80017e8f4a8ebde87136b19da09da67","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1778614963587,"sessionID":"ses_1e24c8305ffeFa590m6IWi1jQq","part":{"id":"prt_e1db6841c001REO4svYLwluD5p","messageID":"msg_e1db3ef0f001dl96jJDR9OM8X1","sessionID":"ses_1e24c8305ffeFa590m6IWi1jQq","type":"text","text":"Prior predictor attempts mostly failed by adding IF next-PC lookup/target logic. I’m writing a narrower predictor hypothesis: exact canonical return prediction from decode using the regfile value, avoiding IF target arrays, branch immediates, or RAS state.","time":{"start":1778614961180,"end":1778614963586},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0de47d216c0542b9016a0382b111d08197a37a0087f54c6778","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778614986670,"sessionID":"ses_1e24c8305ffeFa590m6IWi1jQq","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_P24jiSbKKTfrEApVNadrgJOM","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r12s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r12s2\n+title: \"Decode return target predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor experiments on this core repeatedly lost Fmax by putting\n+  branch target adders, tag compares, BTB/RAS reads, or replay muxing on the\n+  fetch next-PC path. The least costly remaining control-flow opportunity is\n+  canonical function returns: CoreMark still has call/return structure, and a\n+  return target is already available as the decoded rs1 register value for\n+  well-spaced `jalr x0, 0(x1/x5)` instructions.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a decode-stage exact return target predictor for canonical returns only.\n+  When ID sees `jalr x0, 0(x1)` or `jalr x0, 0(x5)`, the instruction is valid,\n+  ID is not stalled/flushed, the rs1 value does not need EX/MEM forwarding, and\n+  the cleared JALR target is word-aligned, redirect IF to that register target\n+  one cycle before the existing EX JALR redirect. Carry a compact predicted-ret\n+  bit and target in ID/EX so EX suppresses the normal redirect only when the\n+  resolved target matches; all forwarded, misaligned, or mismatching cases fall\n+  back to the current EX redirect/trap behavior. This targets return bubbles\n+  with much less timing risk than the failed IF-side RAS, BTB, JAL, loop, and\n+  replay predictors because there is no fetch-stage instruction decode, target\n+  addition, stack lookup, or tag compare on the common fall-through path.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add compact predicted-return metadata to id_ex_t so EX can suppress only matching early return redirects.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Detect aligned canonical returns in decode, gate them on valid/non-stalled state and no required EX/MEM forwarding, emit an early IF redirect target, and latch the prediction metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare predicted return targets against resolved JALR targets and suppress the normal redirect only on exact matches, preserving misalignment traps and RVFI pc_next.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the ID-stage early return redirect to IF with EX redirect priority and without changing the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Accept a gated decode-stage predicted redirect as a lower-priority PC update than EX redirect while keeping ordinary fall-through fetch unchanged.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r12s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r12s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r12s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r12s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,36 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r12s2\n+title: \"Decode return target predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor experiments on this core repeatedly lost Fmax by putting\n+  branch target adders, tag compares, BTB/RAS reads, or replay muxing on the\n+  fetch next-PC path. The least costly remaining control-flow opportunity is\n+  canonical function returns: CoreMark still has call/return structure, and a\n+  return target is already available as the decoded rs1 register value for\n+  well-spaced `jalr x0, 0(x1/x5)` instructions.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a decode-stage exact return target predictor for canonical returns only.\n+  When ID sees `jalr x0, 0(x1)` or `jalr x0, 0(x5)`, the instruction is valid,\n+  ID is not stalled/flushed, the rs1 value does not need EX/MEM forwarding, and\n+  the cleared JALR target is word-aligned, redirect IF to that register target\n+  one cycle before the existing EX JALR redirect. Carry a compact predicted-ret\n+  bit and target in ID/EX so EX suppresses the normal redirect only when the\n+  resolved target matches; all forwarded, misaligned, or mismatching cases fall\n+  back to the current EX redirect/trap behavior. This targets return bubbles\n+  with much less timing risk than the failed IF-side RAS, BTB, JAL, loop, and\n+  replay predictors because there is no fetch-stage instruction decode, target\n+  addition, stack lookup, or tag compare on the common fall-through path.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add compact predicted-return metadata to id_ex_t so EX can suppress only matching early return redirects.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Detect aligned canonical returns in decode, gate them on valid/non-stalled state and no required EX/MEM forwarding, emit an early IF redirect target, and latch the prediction metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare predicted return targets against resolved JALR targets and suppress the normal redirect only on exact matches, preserving misalignment traps and RVFI pc_next.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the ID-stage early return redirect to IF with EX redirect priority and without changing the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Accept a gated decode-stage predicted redirect as a lower-priority PC update than EX redirect while keeping ordinary fall-through fetch unchanged.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r12s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r12s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r12s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r12s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r12s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,36 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r12s2\n+title: \"Decode return target predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor experiments on this core repeatedly lost Fmax by putting\n+  branch target adders, tag compares, BTB/RAS reads, or replay muxing on the\n+  fetch next-PC path. The least costly remaining control-flow opportunity is\n+  canonical function returns: CoreMark still has call/return structure, and a\n+  return target is already available as the decoded rs1 register value for\n+  well-spaced `jalr x0, 0(x1/x5)` instructions.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a decode-stage exact return target predictor for canonical returns only.\n+  When ID sees `jalr x0, 0(x1)` or `jalr x0, 0(x5)`, the instruction is valid,\n+  ID is not stalled/flushed, the rs1 value does not need EX/MEM forwarding, and\n+  the cleared JALR target is word-aligned, redirect IF to that register target\n+  one cycle before the existing EX JALR redirect. Carry a compact predicted-ret\n+  bit and target in ID/EX so EX suppresses the normal redirect only when the\n+  resolved target matches; all forwarded, misaligned, or mismatching cases fall\n+  back to the current EX redirect/trap behavior. This targets return bubbles\n+  with much less timing risk than the failed IF-side RAS, BTB, JAL, loop, and\n+  replay predictors because there is no fetch-stage instruction decode, target\n+  addition, stack lookup, or tag compare on the common fall-through path.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add compact predicted-return metadata to id_ex_t so EX can suppress only matching early return redirects.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Detect aligned canonical returns in decode, gate them on valid/non-stalled state and no required EX/MEM forwarding, emit an early IF redirect target, and latch the prediction metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare predicted return targets against resolved JALR targets and suppress the normal redirect only on exact matches, preserving misalignment traps and RVFI pc_next.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the ID-stage early return redirect to IF with EX redirect priority and without changing the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Accept a gated decode-stage predicted redirect as a lower-priority PC update than EX redirect while keeping ordinary fall-through fetch unchanged.\"\n","additions":36,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r12s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778614986662,"end":1778614986668}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0de47d216c0542b9016a0382b35aec819789d62c808ae16051"}},"id":"prt_e1db68dd7001fJt7oJFUn9PRhk","sessionID":"ses_1e24c8305ffeFa590m6IWi1jQq","messageID":"msg_e1db3ef0f001dl96jJDR9OM8X1"}}
