{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778616620141,"sessionID":"ses_1e2326672ffeu6SPYP8feizLrS","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_vhi9bEIm8WJN21NFM6BKkld9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r13s2.yaml","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r13s2.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: hyp-20260512-003-r13s2\n2: title: \"Speculative EX branch direction\"\n3: category: predictor\n4: motivation: |\n5:   Every prior frontend predictor for this core has lost more FPGA timing than\n6:   it recovered in CoreMark cycles because lookup, target generation, or\n7:   prediction metadata landed on the IF next-PC path. The remaining predictor\n8:   opportunity is to keep fetch as simple fall-through-plus-redirect while\n9:   shortening the EX redirect decision itself.\n10: hypothesis: |\n11:   Predict conditional branch direction in EX with the cheap static heuristic\n12:   already implied by CoreMark loop structure: backward branches predict taken,\n13:   forward branches predict not taken. Use that prediction to drive the EX\n14:   redirect path without waiting for the full rs1/rs2 branch comparator, then\n15:   verify the actual branch condition one stage later in MEM and issue an older\n16:   late redirect on mismatch. Correct backward-loop iterations keep the current\n17:   redirect timing, loop exits pay a one-cycle-later recovery, and the normal IF\n18:   fall-through path gains no BTB, RAS, target-cache, or instruction-predecode\n19:   logic. If the branch comparator/control fanout is part of the current Tang\n20:   Nano critical path, this should trade a small number of extra loop-exit\n21:   bubbles for a modest Fmax gain.\n22: expected_impact:\n23:   fitness_delta_pct: 2\n24:   confidence: low\n25: changes:\n26:   - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n27:     description: \"Add EX/MEM branch prediction metadata and enough branch operand/control fields for MEM-stage verification and correct RVFI pc_wdata.\"\n28:   - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n29:     description: \"Drive conditional-branch redirects from a static backward-taken EX prediction while carrying actual-compare inputs forward instead of resolving redirect from the comparator.\"\n30:   - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n31:     description: \"Verify predicted branch direction, compute the architectural branch pc_next for MEM/WB/RVFI, and expose late-redirect target/mismatch signals.\"\n32:   - file: rtl/core.sv\n33:     description: \"Merge older MEM-stage late redirects with normal EX redirects, giving late branch recovery priority and preserving the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n34:   - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n35:     description: \"Flush younger IF/ID, ID/EX, and EX/MEM work on a MEM-stage branch-prediction mismatch while keeping existing load-use, dmem, imem, and slow-M stalls intact.\"\n\n(End of file - total 35 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260512-003-r13s2\ntitle: \"Speculative EX branch direction\"\ncategory: predictor\nmotivation: |\n  Every prior frontend predictor for this core has lost more FPGA timing than\n  it recovered in CoreMark cycles because lookup, target generation, or\n  prediction metadata landed on the IF next-PC path. The remaining predictor\n  opportunity is to keep fetch as simple fall-through-plus-redirect while\n  shortening the EX redirect decision itself.\nhypothesis: |\n  Predict conditional branch direction in EX with the cheap static heuristic\n  already implied by CoreMark loop structure: backward branches predict taken,\n  forward branches predict not taken. Use that prediction to drive the EX\n  redirect path without waiting for the full rs1/rs2 branch comparator, then\n  verify the actual branch condition one stage later in MEM and issue an older\n  late redirect on mismatch. Correct backward-loop iterations keep the current\n  redirect timing, loop exits pay a one-cycle-later recovery, and the normal IF\n  fall-through path gains no BTB, RAS, target-cache, or instruction-predecode\n  logic. If the branch comparator/control fanout is part of the current Tang\n  Nano critical path, this should trade a small number of extra loop-exit","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r13s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778616620134,"end":1778616620140}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0347a5adecc97774016a03892b59b88198893bd51149c969b4"}},"id":"prt_e1dcfd1e4001iw60lo7VRLUZc3","sessionID":"ses_1e2326672ffeu6SPYP8feizLrS","messageID":"msg_e1dcfb7760015nG7rUNg8EthvJ"}}
