{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778617835036,"sessionID":"ses_1e21fe7dcffedPtIMP3ftGSCbu","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_skO8GX8Xh8MqIYZXfKxbBBUG","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r14s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r14s2\n+title: \"Exact redirect target injector\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The predictor history for this core is dominated by regressions from putting\n+  speculative lookup, target generation, or recovery metadata on the normal\n+  fetch next-PC path. However, CoreMark still pays repeated bubbles on resolved\n+  taken loop branches and unconditional no-link jumps. A narrower predictor-side\n+  opportunity is to use the exact EX redirect target only after the direction\n+  and target are already known, avoiding BTBs, counters, RAS state, and IF-side\n+  immediate decoding.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a non-speculative redirect-target injection path for already-resolved\n+  control transfers that do not write a link register: conditional branches and\n+  JAL x0. When EX asserts such a redirect and imem is ready, temporarily drive\n+  the instruction-memory address with the resolved target, present that target\n+  instruction to decode in the same cycle, and advance the PC to target+4. If\n+  imem is not ready, ID cannot accept, the target is misaligned, or the redirect\n+  is a link-writing JAL/JALR, keep the current bubble-and-fetch behavior. This\n+  should recover one redirect bubble on hot CoreMark loop branches without any\n+  predictor lookup on ordinary fall-through fetches and without the jump-link\n+  forwarding exceptions that hurt earlier JAL/return predictors.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Expose a compact redirect-injection eligibility signal for resolved conditional branches and JAL x0, gated off for misaligned targets and all link-writing jumps.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add an exact redirect-target injection mode that fetches the resolved target instruction in the redirect cycle and advances PC to target+4 only when imem is ready.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Allow the injected redirect target to replace the wrong-path ID payload when the pipeline can accept it; otherwise preserve the existing redirect flush behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the redirect-injection eligibility and accept signals between EX, IF, and hazard control while preserving the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r14s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r14s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r14s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r14s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,34 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r14s2\n+title: \"Exact redirect target injector\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The predictor history for this core is dominated by regressions from putting\n+  speculative lookup, target generation, or recovery metadata on the normal\n+  fetch next-PC path. However, CoreMark still pays repeated bubbles on resolved\n+  taken loop branches and unconditional no-link jumps. A narrower predictor-side\n+  opportunity is to use the exact EX redirect target only after the direction\n+  and target are already known, avoiding BTBs, counters, RAS state, and IF-side\n+  immediate decoding.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a non