{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778618660926,"sessionID":"ses_1e212daacffeptIlsesC5oCuEX","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_7tc4zl6PVJRau2pY4NLEDZ7n","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r15s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r15s2\n+title: \"Accept-gated redirect injector\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts on this core repeatedly lost fitness because they put\n+  target adders, tag compares, counters, RAS reads, or prediction metadata on\n+  the normal fall-through fetch path. The recent exact redirect-target injector\n+  avoided that predictor lookup cost but broke because it could advance the PC\n+  to target+4 while the injected target instruction was still bubbled by ID\n+  flush or accept logic. A corrected version that only injects when decode will\n+  actually capture the target keeps the attractive timing profile while fixing\n+  the known correctness hazard.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add an accept-gated, resolved-target injection path for already-known taken\n+  control transfers, focused on conditional branches and no-link direct JALs.\n+  When EX asserts a redirect, imem is ready, the redirecting instruction has no\n+  link/writeback dependency, and hazard logic proves ID will accept a real\n+  instruction this cycle, IF temporarily addresses the resolved target, presents\n+  that target instruction to decode, and advances the PC to target+4. In every\n+  other case, including any ID hold, load-use bubble, dmem/slow-M stall, imem\n+  stall, misaligned target, link-writing jump, or JALR, the core uses the current\n+  bubble-and-fetch redirect behavior. This is a predictor-side target replay of\n+  an exact resolved redirect, not a speculative branch-direction lookup, so it\n+  should save one bubble on hot CoreMark loop backs without adding work to the\n+  common fall-through next-PC path.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Derive and route an accepted redirect-injection signal only for resolved conditional branches and no-link direct JALs when imem is ready and hazard logic says ID will capture the injected target.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"On accepted injection, drive imem_addr/out.pc from redirect_target, emit the fetched target instruction as valid, and update the PC to redirect_target+4; otherwise preserve existing redirect and stall priority.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Gate redirect flush suppression with the same ID-accept conditions used for stalls and bubbles so an injected target can never be skipped or double-retired.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r15s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r15s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r15s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r15s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,35 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r15s2\n+title: \"Accept-gated redirect injector\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts on this core repeatedly lost fitness because they put\n+  target adders, tag compares, counters, RAS reads, or prediction metadata on\n+  the normal fall-through fetch path. The recent exact redirect-target injector\n+  avoided that predictor lookup cost but broke because it could advance the PC\n+  to target+4 while the injected target instruction was still bubbled by ID\n+  flush or accept logic. A corrected version that only injects when decode will\n+  actually capture the target keeps the attractive timing profile while fixing\n+  the known correctness hazard.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add an accept-gated, resolved-target injection path for already-known taken\n+  control transfers, focused on conditional branches and no-link direct JALs.\n+  When EX asserts a redirect, imem is ready, the redirecting instruction has no\n+  link/writeback dependency, and hazard logic proves ID will accept a real\n+  instruction this cycle, IF temporarily addresses the resolved target, presents\n+  that target instruction to decode, and advances the PC to target+4. In every\n+  other case, including any ID hold, load-use bubble, dmem/slow-M stall, imem\n+  stall, misaligned target, link-writing jump, or JALR, the core uses the current\n+  bubble-and-fetch redirect behavior. This is a predictor-side target replay of\n+  an exact resolved redirect, not a speculative branch-direction lookup, so it\n+  should save one bubble on hot CoreMark loop backs without adding work to the\n+  common fall-through next-PC path.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Derive and route an accepted redirect-injection signal only for resolved conditional branches and no-link direct JALs when imem is ready and hazard logic says ID will capture the injected target.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"On accepted injection, drive imem_addr/out.pc from redirect_target, emit the fetched target instruction as valid, and update the PC to redirect_target+4; otherwise preserve existing redirect and stall priority.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Gate redirect flush suppression with the same ID-accept conditions used for stalls and bubbles so an injected target can never be skipped or double-retired.\"\n\n","files