{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778594815192,"sessionID":"ses_1e37ea033ffeKVuSmoqjrkjzy4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_1JbsbeOxaoVUSkK91OIVS95P","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r1s2\n+title: Static backward-branch next-PC predictor\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current five-stage core resolves all branches and jumps in EX, so every\n+  taken loop branch or direct jump pays the redirect flush penalty. CoreMark is\n+  loop-heavy, and a low-cost predictor that fetches backward branch targets and\n+  direct JAL targets immediately should recover cycles without adding large FPGA\n+  structures or touching the single-retire RVFI contract.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add an IF-stage static next-PC predictor: predict JAL taken, predict\n+  conditional branches with a negative B-immediate taken, and otherwise predict\n+  fall-through. Carry the predicted next PC through IF/ID and ID/EX so EX can\n+  redirect only when the resolved architectural next PC differs from the\n+  prediction. This should turn the common CoreMark loop-back branch from a\n+  taken-branch flush into a correct-path fetch, while forward exits still pay\n+  only the existing mispredict recovery cost.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 6\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add predicted-next-PC metadata to the IF/ID and ID/EX pipeline bundles.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute the static backward-branch/JAL prediction from the fetched instruction and use it for the next PC when not stalled or redirected.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Propagate IF-stage prediction metadata into the ID/EX register alongside the decoded instruction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare resolved next PC against the predicted next PC and redirect only on misprediction or unpredicted JALR.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,29 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r1s2\n+title: Static backward-branch next-PC predictor\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current five-stage core resolves all branches and jumps in EX, so every\n+  taken loop branch or direct jump pays the redirect flush penalty. CoreMark is\n+  loop-heavy, and a low-cost predictor that fetches backward branch targets and\n+  direct JAL targets immediately should recover cycles without adding large FPGA\n+  structures or touching the single-retire RVFI contract.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add an IF-stage static next-PC predictor: predict JAL taken, predict\n+  conditional branches with a negative B-immediate taken, and otherwise predict\n+  fall-through. Carry the predicted next PC through IF/ID and ID/EX so EX can\n+  redirect only when the resolved architectural next PC differs from the\n+  prediction. This should turn the common CoreMark loop-back branch from a\n+  taken-branch flush into a correct-path fetch, while forward exits still pay\n+  only the existing mispredict recovery cost.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 6\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add predicted-next-PC metadata to the IF/ID and ID/EX pipeline bundles.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage