{"type":"text","timestamp":1778596621071,"sessionID":"ses_1e362943fffeFwe3OUbWweIfY1","part":{"id":"prt_e1c9eaa64001oDaT0zFYMgitD6","messageID":"msg_e1c9de2d6002nwDS3G1Otgy5DO","sessionID":"ses_1e362943fffeFwe3OUbWweIfY1","type":"text","text":"Prior predictor evidence points away from IF immediate decoding. I’m writing a BTB-based hypothesis that reuses EX-computed targets, so prediction can save loop redirects without reintroducing the failed IF target-adder critical cone.","time":{"start":1778596620900,"end":1778596621070},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0eff50deec4b38e0016a033b0cc7a48190ab24fa93a6fb1488","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778596641255,"sessionID":"ses_1e362943fffeFwe3OUbWweIfY1","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_tKf2nPunezP9o0TQbvK8mASZ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r2s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r2s2\n+title: \"EX-trained tiny BTB predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The previous static backward-branch predictor recovered some taken-branch\n+  cycles, but it put immediate decode and target addition into the IF next-PC\n+  cone and lost too much Fmax. CoreMark still has hot loop branches and direct\n+  jumps, so the promising predictor direction is to avoid recomputing targets\n+  in IF and instead reuse targets already resolved in EX.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a small direct-mapped branch target buffer with 2-bit taken counters,\n+  trained when branches and jumps resolve in EX. IF predicts taken only on a\n+  valid tag hit whose counter is taken, then uses the stored target directly;\n+  misses fall through to pc+4. Carry the predicted next PC through ID/EX so EX\n+  redirects only when the resolved architectural next PC differs from the\n+  prediction. This should turn steady-state CoreMark loop-back branches into\n+  correct-path fetches while keeping the IF critical path to a tag compare,\n+  counter bit, target mux, and the existing pc+4 adder rather than the failed\n+  immediate-decode plus target-adder cone.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add predicted-next-PC and prediction-valid fields to IF/ID and ID/EX pipeline bundles.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a small EX-trained direct-mapped BTB/BHT and select stored targets on valid taken hits, with fall-through as the default.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Propagate IF prediction metadata into the ID/EX register while preserving existing stall and flush behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare resolved next PC against the carried prediction, redirect on mismatch, and generate BTB/BHT update signals for resolved control-flow instructions.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire EX predictor update signals back to IF and preserve the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r2s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r2s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r2s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r2s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,33 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r2s2\n+title: \"EX-trained tiny BTB predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The previous static backward-branch predictor recovered some taken-branch\n+  cycles, but it put immediate decode and target addition into the IF next-PC\n+  cone and lost too much Fmax. CoreMark still has hot loop branches and direct\n+  jumps, so the promising predictor direction is to avoid recomputing targets\n+  in IF and instead reuse targets already resolved in EX.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a small direct-mapped branch target buffer with 2-bit taken counters,\n+  trained when branches and jumps resolve in EX. IF predicts taken only on a\n+  valid tag hit whose counter is taken, then uses the stored target directly;\n+  misses fall through to pc+4. Carry the predicted next PC through ID/EX so EX\n+  redirects only when the resolved architectural next PC differs from the\n+  prediction. This s