{"type":"text","timestamp":1778598730558,"sessionID":"ses_1e34352caffe3rqZhAPHwKt8bT","part":{"id":"prt_e1cbedad2001Hk7kk56Et5uq6h","messageID":"msg_e1cbd80990019C0JRJxSB22VlA","sessionID":"ses_1e34352caffe3rqZhAPHwKt8bT","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a narrow predictor hypothesis: a single-entry backward-loop target latch trained in EX, avoiding IF immediate decode and BTB arrays while still targeting CoreMark’s hot loop back-edges.","time":{"start":1778598730450,"end":1778598730557},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0b6301e8751433cf016a03434a51bc8195adad40b6283ce640","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778598749311,"sessionID":"ses_1e34352caffe3rqZhAPHwKt8bT","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_I9bgosV9Uc2KZbSplykhmWAt","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r3s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r3s2\n+title: \"Single-entry loop target predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts recovered some control-flow cycles but lost fitness by\n+  putting too much work in the fetch next-PC path: immediate target calculation\n+  for static prediction, then tag/counter/target array lookup for a tiny BTB.\n+  CoreMark is still loop-heavy, so the best remaining predictor angle is a much\n+  narrower loop-back predictor that only remembers one resolved backward branch\n+  target and avoids any IF instruction decode or target addition.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry EX-trained backward-loop target latch. When EX resolves a\n+  taken conditional branch whose target is below its PC, record {branch_pc,\n+  branch_target}; when IF later fetches the same PC, predict the stored target.\n+  Clear or mark not-taken when that same branch resolves fall-through so loop\n+  exits recover after one mispredict. Carry predicted-next-PC metadata through\n+  ID/EX so EX suppresses redirects on correct predictions and redirects only on\n+  mismatches. This should save repeated inner-loop taken-branch bubbles with far\n+  less fetch-side cost than the failed static predictor or BTB.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add predicted-next-PC metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles for one-entry loop prediction verification in EX.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a single-entry backward-loop target latch trained by EX and use it only on exact PC hits, with fall-through as the default.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Propagate IF prediction metadata into the ID/EX register without changing decode legality or RVFI source fields.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Train/clear the loop target latch from resolved conditional branches and redirect only when resolved next PC differs from the prediction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire EX predictor training signals to IF while preserving the nret=1 RVFI top-level contract.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r3s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r3s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r3s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r3s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,33 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r3s2\n+title: \"Single-entry loop target predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts recovered some control-flow cycles but lost fitness by\n+  putting too much work in the fetch next-PC path: immediate target calculation\n+  for static prediction, then tag/counter/target array lookup for a tiny BTB.\n+  CoreMark is still loop-heavy, so the best remaining predictor angle is a much\n+  narrower loop-back predictor that only remembers one resolved backward branch\n+  target and avoids any IF instruction decode or target addition.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry EX-trained backward-loop target latch. When EX resolves a\n+  taken conditional branch whose target is below its PC, record {branch_pc,\n+  branch_target}; when IF later fetches the same PC, predict the stored targe