{"type":"text","timestamp":1778601653521,"sessionID":"ses_1e31751d7ffeBrKnCXejGpl9QL","part":{"id":"prt_e1ceb74c1001SGTs22Tzul28Ae","messageID":"msg_e1ce918e6001w7UQeDgpkWqqj5","sessionID":"ses_1e31751d7ffeBrKnCXejGpl9QL","type":"text","text":"Prior predictor attempts all paid too much fetch-path timing cost. I’m writing a narrower predictor hypothesis that only predicts aligned direct `JAL` targets in decode, avoiding BTB/RAS state and conditional-branch direction logic.","time":{"start":1778601653441,"end":1778601653521},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_010689866c5c7879016a034eb54ca48197a0d25edab25da944","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778601673251,"sessionID":"ses_1e31751d7ffeBrKnCXejGpl9QL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_fwWuqjsbvxhDqdQ5h92L4KXR","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r5s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r5s2\n+title: \"Decode-stage JAL target predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts lost fitness because they put branch immediate decode,\n+  tag compares, target arrays, or RAS logic directly in the fetch next-PC path.\n+  CoreMark still contains direct calls and unconditional jumps, and those are\n+  deterministic once the instruction is visible in decode. A narrower predictor\n+  can recover some redirect bubbles without adding conditional branch direction\n+  state or a BTB-style lookup to every fetch.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add an early direct-JAL target predictor in decode: when ID sees an aligned\n+  JAL instruction, compute pc+J_imm using the existing decoded immediate path\n+  and redirect IF one stage earlier than the normal EX redirect. Carry a compact\n+  predicted-direct-jump bit and predicted target through ID/EX so EX suppresses\n+  the ordinary JAL redirect when the prediction matches, and recovers normally\n+  for misaligned targets or any mismatch. This focuses the predictor on\n+  unconditional direct control flow, avoiding the failed conditional-branch,\n+  loop-BTB, and RAS structures while still saving bubbles on CoreMark calls and\n+  direct jumps.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add compact direct-JAL prediction metadata to IF/ID or ID/EX pipeline bundles for EX redirect suppression and recovery.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Detect aligned JAL instructions in decode, compute the early target from the existing immediate path, and emit prediction metadata with the instruction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the decode-stage predicted redirect into the IF stage with EX redirect taking priority, preserving nret=1 RVFI retirement semantics.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Accept an early predicted redirect target while keeping reset, stalls, and resolved EX redirects prioritized for correctness.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Suppress the normal JAL redirect when decode prediction matches the resolved target; otherwise use the existing redirect recovery and misalignment trap behavior.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r5s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r5s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r5s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r5s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,34 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r5s2\n+title: \"Decode-stage JAL target predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts lost fitness because they put branch immediate decode,\n+  tag compares, target arrays, or RAS logic directly in the fetch next-PC path.\n+  CoreMark still contains direct calls and unconditional jumps, and those are\n+  deterministic once the instruction is visible in decode. A narrower predictor\n+  can recover some redirect bubbles without adding conditional branch direction\n+  state or a BTB-style lookup to every fetch.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add an early direct-JAL target predictor in decode: when ID sees an aligned\n+  JAL instruction, compute pc+J_imm using the existing