{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778603238999,"sessionID":"ses_1e2fed6b7ffe97xjpoVKWRiGv7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_X2txpUfg8qQbAeoohMDRy2JO","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r6s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r6s2\n+title: \"Countdown loop predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts recovered possible control-flow cycles but lost more\n+  FPGA fitness through fetch-side instruction decode, target adders, BTB/RAS\n+  lookup, or exact PC compare paths. CoreMark is still loop-heavy, so the most\n+  promising remaining predictor angle is to keep loop prediction state cheap\n+  enough that it does not dominate the IF next-PC cone.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry backward-loop countdown predictor trained by EX when a\n+  conditional branch resolves taken to a lower PC. Store the loop target and\n+  the branch-to-target distance in words, then count sequential fetch advances\n+  from the target; when the counter reaches zero, predict the stored loop\n+  target without decoding the fetched instruction or comparing the fetch PC\n+  against a tag. Carry compact prediction metadata through ID/EX so EX can\n+  suppress the normal taken-branch redirect on a correct loop prediction and\n+  recover to pc+4 on the loop exit or any mismatch. This should preserve most\n+  of the useful inner-loop benefit of the failed loop/BTB predictors while\n+  replacing the IF exact-PC/tag compare with a small zero-count check.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add compact predicted-loop-taken and predicted-target metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add the single-entry backward-loop countdown predictor, update it on resolved branch training, and select the stored target only when the countdown reaches zero.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Propagate the IF-stage loop prediction metadata through the ID/EX register without changing decode legality behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Expose backward-branch training information and use the carried prediction metadata to suppress correct predicted-loop redirects or recover on loop exit/mismatch.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire EX loop-training signals back to IF while preserving the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r6s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r6s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r6s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r6s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,34 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r6s2\n+title: \"Countdown loop predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts recovered possible control-flow cycles but lost more\n+  FPGA fitness through fetch-side instruction decode, target adders, BTB/RAS\n+  lookup, or exact PC compare paths. CoreMark is still loop-heavy, so the most\n+  promising remaining predictor angle is to keep loop prediction state cheap\n+  enough that it does not dominate the IF next-PC cone.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry backward-loop countdown predictor trained by EX when a\n+  conditional branch resolves taken to a lower PC. Store the loop target and\n+  the branch-to-target distance in words, then count sequential fetch advances\n+  from the target; when the c