{"type":"text","timestamp":1778604575944,"sessionID":"ses_1e2e9e5b5ffeMIupVvztGxWmbr","part":{"id":"prt_e1d18070c001aA7LEx6Xo4JfWH","messageID":"msg_e1d169344001M6PdBkJrHkWhGj","sessionID":"ses_1e2e9e5b5ffeMIupVvztGxWmbr","type":"text","text":"Prior predictor logs consistently point to the same failure mode: useful branch bubbles exist, but anything that puts decode, compare, target lookup, or target add back into the live IF next-PC cone loses Fmax. I’m going to write a predictor hypothesis that keeps loop prediction but retimes the lookup one cycle ahead so the PC update uses only registered hit/target state.","time":{"start":1778604574476,"end":1778604575943},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_016e4831d751ae24016a035a1e5664819097afa1bcaad6bcd0","phase":"commentary"}}}}
