{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778604628734,"sessionID":"ses_1e2e9e5b5ffeMIupVvztGxWmbr","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_kg2We7cgeEY5i22B4zFMr8FP","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r7s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r7s2\n+title: \"Registered lookahead loop predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  CoreMark is still loop-heavy, so the remaining control-flow opportunity is\n+  reducing repeated taken backward-branch redirects. The prior predictor\n+  attempts show that the useful predictor must not put instruction decode,\n+  target adders, BTB tag compares, or RAS reads on the same-cycle IF next-PC\n+  path, because Fmax loss dominates the saved bubbles.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a tiny EX-trained backward-loop predictor whose lookup is performed one\n+  fetch ahead for the next sequential PC and latched before it can affect the\n+  PC update. While fetching PC P, IF compares the trained loop branch PC\n+  against P+4 and captures a registered hit/target for the instruction that\n+  will be fetched next; when that next instruction is actually at the\n+  loop-branch PC, the PC update selects the already-registered target with no\n+  live tag compare or target-array read in the PC feedback cone. EX trains the\n+  entry on taken backward conditional branches and invalidates it when the same\n+  branch resolves not taken, while carried prediction metadata lets EX suppress\n+  correct predicted redirects or recover normally on loop exit. This keeps the\n+  predictor focused on hot loop-back branches and directly addresses the timing\n+  failure mode of the earlier static, BTB, RAS, and countdown predictors.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add compact predicted-taken and predicted-target fields to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles so EX can verify a registered loop prediction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a one-entry backward-loop predictor, do the PC/tag comparison against the next sequential PC one cycle ahead, and use only registered hit/target state in the PC update path.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Expose conditional-branch training information and suppress or recover redirects by comparing the resolved next PC against carried prediction metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Propagate prediction metadata from IF into the ID/EX register across existing stall and flush behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire EX branch-training signals into IF while preserving the nret=1 top-level IO contract.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r7s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r7s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r7s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r7s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,36 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r7s2\n+title: \"Registered lookahead loop predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  CoreMark is still loop-heavy, so the remaining control-flow opportunity is\n+  reducing repeated taken backward-branch redirects. The prior predictor\n+  attempts show that the useful predictor must not put instruction decode,\n+  target adders, BTB tag compares, or RAS reads on the same-cycle IF next-PC\n+  path, because Fmax loss dominates the saved bubbles.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a tiny EX-trained backward-loop predictor whose lookup is performed one\n+  fetch ahead for the next sequential PC and latched before it can affect the\n+  PC update. While fetching PC P, IF compares the trained loop branch PC\n+  against P+4 and captures a registered hit/target for the instruction that\n+  will be fetched next; when that next instruction is actually at the\n+  loop-branch PC, the PC update selects the already-registered target with no\n+  live tag compare or target-array read in the PC feedback cone. EX trains the\n+  entry on taken backward conditional branches and invalidates it when the same\n+  branch resolves not taken, while carried prediction metadata lets EX suppress\n+  correct predicted redirects or recover normally on loop exit. This keeps the\n+  predictor focused on hot loop-back branches and directly addresses the timing\n+  failure mode of the earlier static, BTB, RAS, and countdown predictors.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add compact predicted-taken and predicted-target fields to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles so EX can verify a registered loop prediction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a one-entry backward-loop predictor, do the PC/tag comparison against the next sequential PC one cycle ahead, and use only registered hit/target state in the PC update path.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Expose conditional-branch training information and suppress or recover redirects by comparing the resolved next PC against carried prediction metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Propagate prediction metadata from IF into the ID/EX register across existing stall and flush behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire EX branch-training signals into IF while preserving the nret=1 top-level IO contract.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r7s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r7s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r7s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r7s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r7s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,36 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r7s2\n+title: \"Registered lookahead loop predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  CoreMark is still loop-heavy, so the remaining control-flow opportunity is\n+  reducing repeated taken backward-branch redirects. The prior predictor\n+  attempts show that the useful predictor must not put instruction decode,\n+  target adders, BTB tag compares, or RAS reads on the same-cycle IF next-PC\n+  path, because Fmax loss dominates the saved bubbles.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a tiny EX-trained backward-loop predictor whose lookup is performed one\n+  fetch ahead for the next sequential PC and latched before it can affect the\n+  PC update. While fetching PC P, IF compares the trained loop branch PC\n+  against P+4 and captures a registered hit/target for the instruction that\n+  will be fetched next; when that next instruction is actually at the\n+  loop-branch PC, the PC update selects the already-registered target with no\n+  live tag compare or target-array read in the PC feedback cone. EX trains the\n+  entry on taken backward conditional branches and invalidates it when the same\n+  branch resolves not taken, while carried prediction metadata lets EX suppress\n+  correct predicted redirects or recover normally on loop exit. This keeps the\n+  predictor focused on hot loop-back branches and directly addresses the timing\n+  failure mode of the earlier static, BTB, RAS, and countdown predictors.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add compact predicted-taken and predicted-target fields to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles so EX can verify a registered loop prediction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a one-entry backward-loop predictor, do the PC/tag comparison against the next sequential PC one cycle ahead, and use only registered hit/target state in the PC update path.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Expose conditional-branch training information and suppress or recover redirects by comparing the resolved next PC against carried prediction metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Propagate prediction metadata from IF into the ID/EX register across existing stall and flush behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire EX branch-training signals into IF while preserving the nret=1 top-level IO contract.\"\n","additions":36,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r7s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778604628731,"end":1778604628734}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0ce6bc0e1dae79e1016a035a3eecf48195bcc15c67c90e1591"}},"id":"prt_e1d188634001SwuizGgg6YCBb6","sessionID":"ses_1e2e9e5b5ffeMIupVvztGxWmbr","messageID":"msg_e1d18155e001mGTYw9l90DO3uY"}}
