{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778604642689,"sessionID":"ses_1e2e9e5b5ffeMIupVvztGxWmbr","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Imv63CiMkkAhe9uTy3RNy0lk","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r7s2.yaml","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r7s2.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: hyp-20260512-003-r7s2\n2: title: \"Registered lookahead loop predictor\"\n3: category: predictor\n4: motivation: |\n5:   CoreMark is still loop-heavy, so the remaining control-flow opportunity is\n6:   reducing repeated taken backward-branch redirects. The prior predictor\n7:   attempts show that the useful predictor must not put instruction decode,\n8:   target adders, BTB tag compares, or RAS reads on the same-cycle IF next-PC\n9:   path, because Fmax loss dominates the saved bubbles.\n10: hypothesis: |\n11:   Add a tiny EX-trained backward-loop predictor whose lookup is performed one\n12:   fetch ahead for the next sequential PC and latched before it can affect the\n13:   PC update. While fetching PC P, IF compares the trained loop branch PC\n14:   against P+4 and captures a registered hit/target for the instruction that\n15:   will be fetched next; when that next instruction is actually at the\n16:   loop-branch PC, the PC update selects the already-registered target with no\n17:   live tag compare or target-array read in the PC feedback cone. EX trains the\n18:   entry on taken backward conditional branches and invalidates it when the same\n19:   branch resolves not taken, while carried prediction metadata lets EX suppress\n20:   correct predicted redirects or recover normally on loop exit. This keeps the\n21:   predictor focused on hot loop-back branches and directly addresses the timing\n22:   failure mode of the earlier static, BTB, RAS, and countdown predictors.\n23: expected_impact:\n24:   fitness_delta_pct: 2\n25:   confidence: low\n26: changes:\n27:   - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n28:     description: \"Add compact predicted-taken and predicted-target fields to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles so EX can verify a registered loop prediction.\"\n29:   - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n30:     description: \"Add a one-entry backward-loop predictor, do the PC/tag comparison against the next sequential PC one cycle ahead, and use only registered hit/target state in the PC update path.\"\n31:   - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n32:     description: \"Expose conditional-branch training information and suppress or recover redirects by comparing the resolved next PC against carried prediction metadata.\"\n33:   - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n34:     description: \"Propagate prediction metadata from IF into the ID/EX register across existing stall and flush behavior.\"\n35:   - file: rtl/core.sv\n36:     description: \"Wire EX branch-training signals into IF while preserving the nret=1 top-level IO contract.\"\n\n(End of file - total 36 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260512-003-r7s2\ntitle: \"Registered lookahead loop predictor\"\ncategory: predictor\nmotivation: |\n  CoreMark is still loop-heavy, so the remaining control-flow opportunity is\n  reducing repeated taken backward-branch redirects. The prior predictor\n  attempts show that the useful predictor must not put instruction decode,\n  target adders, BTB tag compares, or RAS reads on the same-cycle IF next-PC\n  path, because Fmax loss dominates the saved bubbles.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a tiny EX-trained backward-loop predictor whose lookup is performed one\n  fetch ahead for the next sequential PC and latched before it can affect the\n  PC update. While fetching PC P, IF compares the trained loop branch PC\n  against P+4 and captures a registered hit/target for the instruction that\n  will be fetched next; when that next instruction is actually at the\n  loop-branch PC, the PC update selects the already-registered target with no\n  live tag compare or target-array read in the PC feedback cone. EX trains the\n  entry on taken backward conditional branches and invalidates it when the same\n  branch resolves not taken, while carried prediction metadata lets EX suppress\n  correct predicted redirects or recover normally on loop exit. This keeps the","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r7s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778604642678,"end":1778604642688}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0ae30a34bab28b41016a035a62918c819791384e39e04ecf7c"}},"id":"prt_e1d191161001BJw9F3V5MEAS1e","sessionID":"ses_1e2e9e5b5ffeMIupVvztGxWmbr","messageID":"msg_e1d18db95001bsOkclf4m3IyAA"}}
