{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778606907249,"sessionID":"ses_1e2ca626fffeExf3EPXJIrSnI3","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_hTojdi6tg1mQ2ZRkgBjSbsNw","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r8s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r8s2\n+title: \"JAL-only target cache\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts show that CoreMark does not repay broad IF-stage\n+  branch machinery: static backward prediction, BTBs, loop predictors, and RAS\n+  variants all lost Fmax through target adders, tag/counter lookup, recovery\n+  metadata, or extra next-PC muxing. The remaining control-flow predictor angle\n+  with a plausible timing budget is to predict only direct JAL instructions,\n+  which are unconditionally taken and do not need direction counters or branch\n+  condition state.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a tiny EX-trained target cache for aligned direct JAL/JAL-x0 instructions\n+  only. When EX resolves an aligned direct JAL, store its PC signature and\n+  resolved target in a two-entry cache; when IF fetches a JAL opcode with a\n+  matching signature, use the stored target and carry compact predicted-JAL\n+  metadata to EX. EX suppresses the normal redirect when the stored target\n+  matches the resolved JAL target, and otherwise falls back to the existing\n+  redirect/trap path. This avoids the failed static predictor's IF immediate\n+  decode and target adder, avoids BTB direction counters, avoids conditional\n+  branch prediction entirely, and targets only always-taken call/jump bubbles\n+  that can be recovered with minimal predictor state.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add compact predicted-JAL and predicted-target fields to the IF/ID and ID/EX bundles.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add the two-entry direct-JAL target cache, JAL opcode/signature lookup, predicted next-PC selection, and EX training inputs.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Propagate predicted-JAL metadata into ID/EX without changing decode legality or source operand handling.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Train the JAL target cache on aligned direct JAL resolution and suppress or recover redirects based on predicted-target match.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire direct-JAL prediction metadata and EX training signals while preserving the nret=1 RVFI top-level port contract.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r8s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r8s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r8s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r8s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,36 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r8s2\n+title: \"JAL-only target cache\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts show that CoreMark does not repay broad IF-stage\n+  branch machinery: static backward prediction, BTBs, loop predictors, and RAS\n+  variants all lost Fmax through target adders, tag/counter lookup, recovery\n+  metadata, or extra next-PC muxing. The remaining control-flow predictor angle\n+  with a plausible timing budget is to predict only direct JAL instructions,\n+  which are unconditionally taken and do not need direction counters or branch\n+  condition state.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a tiny EX-trained target cache for aligned direct JAL/JAL-x0 instructions\n+  only. When EX resolves an aligned direct JAL, store its PC signature and\n+  resolved target in a two-entry cache; when IF fetches a JAL opcode with a\n+  matching signature, use the stored target and carry compact predicted-JAL\n+  metadata to EX. EX suppresses the normal redirect when the stored target\n+  matches the resolved JAL target, and otherwise falls back to the existing\n+  redirect/trap path. This avoids the failed static predictor's IF immediate\n+  decode and target adder, avoids BTB direction counters, avoids conditional\n+  branch prediction entirely, and targets only always-taken call/jump bubbles\n+  that can be recovered with minimal predictor state.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add compact predicted-JAL and predicted-target fields to the IF/ID and ID/EX bundles.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add the two-entry direct-JAL target cache, JAL opcode/signature lookup, predicted next-PC selection, and EX training inputs.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Propagate predicted-JAL metadata into ID/EX without changing decode legality or source operand handling.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Train the JAL target cache on aligned direct JAL resolution and suppress or recover redirects based on predicted-target match.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire direct-JAL prediction metadata and EX training signals while preserving the nret=1 RVFI top-level port contract.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r8s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r8s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r8s2.yaml\n===============================