{"type":"text","timestamp":1778608799982,"sessionID":"ses_1e2ab04c2ffeTIE1gla72j4sx1","part":{"id":"prt_e1d587874001joDRjypgw4457V","messageID":"msg_e1d557a32001Rrk06F5J3lY5XU","sessionID":"ses_1e2ab04c2ffeTIE1gla72j4sx1","type":"text","text":"Prior predictor attempts consistently regressed when lookup, target add, or metadata sat on the normal IF next-PC path. I’m writing a narrower stall-shadow predictor hypothesis that only computes a registered prediction while fetch is already held, aiming to avoid the always-on IF timing penalty.","time":{"start":1778608797812,"end":1778608799981},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0c16890b72f1574d016a036a9d9ec4819684ad033e318f406f","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778608821545,"sessionID":"ses_1e2ab04c2ffeTIE1gla72j4sx1","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_CsSt2hklItBKNVShpT9wTFqF","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r9s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r9s2\n+title: \"Stall-shadow branch predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts on this core lost fitness because they put target\n+  adders, tag compares, counters, return-stack reads, or prediction recovery\n+  muxes on the normal IF next-PC path. The random-stall CoreMark methodology\n+  still creates cycles where IF is holding a valid instruction while decode,\n+  dmem, or a slow M operation is stalled. Those otherwise idle hold cycles can\n+  be used to prepare a prediction without making every fetch pay the full\n+  predictor timing cost.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add an opportunistic stall-shadow predictor that only arms while IF is\n+  stalled on a valid held instruction. During the hold window, predecode only\n+  aligned direct JALs and negative-immediate conditional branches, compute the\n+  static taken target, and store that target in a small registered shadow slot.\n+  When the stall releases for the same held PC/instruction, IF selects the\n+  already-registered target and carries compact predicted-next-PC metadata to\n+  EX. EX suppresses the normal redirect when the resolved next PC matches the\n+  shadow prediction and recovers through the existing flush path on mismatch or\n+  loop exit. This targets control-flow bubbles that immediately follow existing\n+  load-use, dmem, imem, or slow-M stalls while avoiding live predictor lookup,\n+  immediate decode, and target addition on ordinary fall-through fetch cycles.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add compact predicted-next-PC metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles for shadow-prediction validation in EX.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add the stall-shadow predictor: predecode held JAL/backward-branch instructions during stalls, register aligned targets, and use the registered target only when the same held instruction is released.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Propagate shadow prediction metadata through the ID/EX register while preserving existing stall and flush behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare resolved next PC against shadow-predicted next PC to suppress correct redirects and recover normally on mismatches, misaligned targets, or loop exits.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r9s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r9s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r9s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r9s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,35 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r9s2\n+title: \"Stall-shadow branch predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts on this core lost fitness because they put target\n+  adders, tag compares, counters, return-stack reads, or prediction recovery\n+  muxes on the normal IF next-PC path. The random-stall CoreMark methodology\n+  still creates cycles where IF is holding a valid instruction while decode,\n+  dmem, or a slow M operation is stalled. Those otherwise idle hold cycles can\n+  be used to prepare a prediction without making every fetch pay the full\n+  predictor timing cost.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add an opportunistic stall-shadow predictor that only arms while IF is\n+  stalled on a valid held instruction. During the hold window, predecode only\n+  aligned direct JALs and negative-immediate conditional branches, compute the\n+  static taken target, and store that target in a small registered shadow slot.\n+  When the stall releases for the same held PC/instruction, IF selects the\n+  already-registered target and carries compact predicted-next-PC metadata to\n+  EX. EX suppresses the normal redirect when the resolved next PC matches the\n+  shadow prediction and recovers through the existing flush path on mismatch or\n+  loop exit. This targets control-flow bubbles that immediately follow existing\n+  load-use, dmem, imem, or slow-M stalls while avoiding live predictor lookup,\n+  immediate decode, and target addition on ordinary fall-through fetch cycles.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add compact predicted-next-PC metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles for shadow-prediction validation in EX.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add the stall-shadow predictor: predecode held JAL/backward-branch instructions during stalls, register aligned targets, and use the registered target only when the same held instruction is released.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Propagate shadow prediction metadata through the ID/EX register while preserving existing stall and flush behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare resolved next PC against shadow-predicted next PC to suppress correct redirects and recover normally on mismatches, misaligned targets, or loop exits.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r9s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r9s2.yaml","type":"add